title: TUFF CLUB @ Oxley Tower
text:
Visited Tuff Club with two friends on a weekend evening, and unfortunately, this venue falls well short of Singapore's nightlife standards.

Entry & Pricing
Upon arrival, we were offered two options: $60 standard entry or $80 with bar coupons. We opted for the latter, assuming it would provide better value ‚Äì a decision we quickly regretted. The coupon system felt like a marketing gimmick rather than genuine added value.

Atmosphere & Crowd
The venue was surprisingly sparse, with fewer than 30 patrons despite the modest space. Even accounting for the club's compact size, the atmosphere felt lifeless and lacking the energy you'd expect from a proper nightlife venue. The sparse crowd made the evening feel more awkward than intimate.

Interior & Cleanliness
The bar area desperately needs renovation ‚Äì the aesthetic can only be described as dated and uninspiring, reminiscent of an old Eastern Bloc establishment. More concerning was the cleanliness standard: our table left black residue on contact, suggesting poor maintenance and hygiene practices. This immediately raised red flags about the venue's upkeep.

Facilities
The restroom facilities were particularly disappointing ‚Äì cramped, unclean, and genuinely uncomfortable to use. For a venue charging premium entry prices, basic cleanliness should be non-negotiable.
Redeeming Features
The only highlight was the outdoor terrace area, which provided a brief respite from the indoor environment and served as a decent smoking area.

Verdict
After less than an hour, our group decided to cut our losses and leave. For $80 per person, there are numerous superior venues in Singapore that offer better atmosphere, cleanliness, and overall experience. Tuff Club needs significant improvements in maintenance, crowd management, and basic hygiene standards before it can compete with the city's established nightlife scene.
Would I return? Definitely not.
Would I recommend? Only if you're specifically looking for a cautionary tale about Singapore's nightlife scene.

title: TUFF CLUB @ Oxley Tower
text:
My god ‚Äî Tuff Club is easily one of my FAVORITE clubs in Singapore!! This was my first time going and I‚Äôm already planning my return. The music was absolutely on point ‚Äî deep, groovy, and so well-curated. If you're into quality electronic / techno / house music, this place delivers. The vibe is super cool, energetic but not chaotic, and everyone there just gets it.

Bonus point: met so many fun people here ‚Äî apparently a lot of folks who didn‚Äôt get into Rabbit Hole (the new viral gay club) end up here, so... yes, the eye candy is real üòÜ but even beyond that, the crowd was fun, respectful, and full of good energy.

Also, shoutout to the fact that they have an OUTDOOR SMOKING AREA ‚Äî yes!!! You can actually step out, get some air, and still be part of the vibe. It's little things like this that make a night out feel just right.

All in all ‚Äî music, crowd, atmosphere, energy ‚Äî everything was perfect. I‚Äôm in love with this place. See you again soon, Tuff Club!!!

title: Chye Seng Huat Hardware
text:
I had a Suke Quto coffee, grown in Ethiopian highlands: the coffee was elegantly presented in a clear glass flask wrapped with a scarf, with a product description card, a ceramic mug, all on a wooden tray.
Described as Peach and Earl Gray and Citrus, my untrained palate could not quite discern: but it was a pleasant light black coffee: smelt fragrant. Wife had an iced cafe latte, daughter a flat white. All beverages 10/10. We shared a scrambled egg on croissant, (croissant 10/10, scrambled 8/10),  and a triple cheese grilled sourdough sandwich (10/10) served with a nice apple salad (10/10)

The place is like a three ring circus with lots of things going on. There is the courtyard outdoor area where we were seated (inside was full at 10 am on a Tuesday). It is open during the day and transforms into a beer garden in the evenings, providing a different atmosphere.

There is the indoor seated aircon area dubbed the coffee bar: A U-shaped bar where baristas prepare coffee, offering a 360-degree view of the brewing process. It also features an all-day menu with baked goods.

There is the Annex, a retail space where customers can find a range of coffee products, accessories, and equipment. Coffee specialists are available to provide advice and guidance.¬†‚Ä®‚Ä®Then there is the roastery. This area is dedicated to the process of roasting coffee beans, showcasing the journey from bean to cup.¬†What really caught my attention at CSHH was the massive Probat 45G Roaster.

The Probate G45 Roaster designed to handle a batch capacity of 45 Kg, although the staff told me they prefer to process a maximum of 30 kg of coffee beans at a time. When I was sketching, Aroy was manning the complex computer control. Some of the cafe staff were attracted to my antics and came to take photos.

Educational value 10/10
Entertainment value 10/10
Ambiance 10/10
Parking ease (10 am) easy 10/10
Damage to pocket: ouch, but you get for what you pay. About $20 per pax.

text: Visited this workshop from a friend referral and was attended by the boss, Roy from Zenith Auotmotive. Very dissapointed with the repairs as a simple job of removing headlights took 2 days. Worse part is the issue came back right after I drove the car home and a hefty bill was invoiced to me for the long manhours which only took 15 minutes to resolve (a connector wasn't plug-in fully) after the second time I went back to get it looked at again and insisted to stay and watch the mechanic work on it. Thankfully wasn't charged on the second visit but left angry and never to patronize the shop ever again. Extremely terrible experience and utter waste of money.

title: Zenith Automotive Services
text:
i go to them not because they are efficient.
i go to them not because they are honest.
i go to them not because they are competitively priced.

i go to them because i know i have peace of mind to send my car there.

for example, today i have 2 CELs on and i didn't make any booking. Just drove over and asked Uncle Roy for help.

title: Zenith Automotive Services
text: Repair at your own risk. Roy from Zenith Auotmotive appeared to be ‚ÄúMr Nice Guy‚Äù but he is actually a wolf under a sheep skin. Zenith Automotive is managed by Roy, his wife, his son and daughters. I‚Äôve been repairing my car at zenith for more than 5 years. My whole family too as we are all staying nearby. He was introduced to us by our Cycle&Carriage salesperson Han Ai Lin. At first, he appeared to be very nice and honest. But after a few repairs, I felt that something was off. Everytime we repair a problem, a new problem will arise. At first I thought it was pure coincidence but this not only happened to me all the time, but also my dad‚Äôs, my mum‚Äôs and my sis‚Äôs car. The last I remembered was I repaired my aircon at Zenith, 1-2 days after car collection, my engine starts to make weird sounds. His charges seemed to be reasonable like repair for the aircon $800 but in the end I always have to add on another few thousands. This didn‚Äôt happen once, it happened many times. This time, I went to repair my new car as my husband has met a small accident. He repaired my bumper for few hundred dollars. He said he repaired the headlamp mounting too. After awhile, our headlights starts to turn misty and the headlights was damaged due to the mist. We went back to Cycle & Carriage and they mentioned that it was because Zenith did not repair it properly, he simply use a glue to repair the mounting, resulting the headlights to have mist and damage it. I have asked a few more workshops and they said the same thing. So his style is to charge a reasonable amount and so you have more new problems and go back and pay more money for the repair. I‚Äôve asked a few workshop friends and realised that he is well-known to be dishonest in the industry. Please do not be fooled by them anymore!!!

title: Zenith Automotive Services
text: We‚Äôve had a very terrible experience with Zenith, serviced by Roy. We brought the car in and mentioned that there was noise on the front right tyre / suspension and notification on the dashboard that there‚Äôs increase in battery discharge when car is stationary even though our battery was changed only 5 months ago. Zenith told us to change front shock absorber and battery. We paid $1,110 for the change. After taking the car back the noise on the tyre was still not resolved, we brought it in and he said he lubricated it so should be ok. But it was not. We brought the car back for the third time and asked to pay another $480 to change something else. We negotiated the price and still paid. 1 month later, the notification on dashboard for battery discharge came up AGAIN. We brought it back in and asked to pay another $200 and they provided the battery life and diagnostics showing another problem. We paid but no idea whether the problem is actually fixed or not.. When I asked him about the battery life and diagnostics on the first visit when we were advised to change the new battery, they gave me a lecture about mutual trust and did not show it (lol). So both our problems when we first brought the car in were not fixed in first visit and we kept going back to check and top up later. Please be careful when dealing with them because you have no idea whether you are paying for the actual fix or not and they don‚Äôt seem to do their diagnostics well!

title: MY Clinic
text:
I only used this clinic because they were the only ones in my neighbourhood on my corporate insurance panel.  Pretty average standard level of expertise for GPs. The doctors there are friendly enough, although the clinic always looked messy.

I opted to use them for Healthier SG programme, after the lead GP sold me a very nice pitch. that was in Dec 2023.  I was also encouraged to email them, which i did. I sent an email on 2 Jan 2024, which went on to be unanswered for MONTHS.  Follow up emails and even phone calls were unanswered and when I finally managed to get through, it was already 19 July 2023.  All i got from the receptionist Lavina was "did you?" when I told her about the email.

So apparently no one checks the only email account of the clinic but Lavina. Either that, my email is not deemed important enough to open.  In the end, my treatment was kept in status quo and I didnt start my HSG programme till much later.

When queried, all i got was a very insincere "As spoken on the phone on 20 July 2024, we have conveyed our apologies and we are again sorry to hear of the cost concerns with your specialist", without the lead GP even acknowleging that his team messed up and dropped the ball on me. The fact that my emails and calls were unanswered for more than 7 months was the MAIN ISSUE, which the clinic didnt want to address. I am pretty sure if i hadnt called, it would have gone on to remain unanswered.

I was told in an email on 22 July 2024 that the delay was due to the clinic having to "clarify a few things with ALPs and AIC as to the drugs eligible under HSG". It must have been arduous, having to require more than 7 months.

I have since enrolled with another clinic for HSG. They are further away from my home, but at least the Physician there follows up on me regularly.  I feel very cared for by my new Physician, who clearly is invested in my welbeing.  I guess when you put patient's needs before monetary gains, this will happen.

Sometimes, it is better to just admit mistakes and not deny making them.

title: Italian Coffee Lab Singapore
text:
I first stumbled upon Italian Coffee Lab through an Instagram video. So on the eve of National Day, my colleagues and I decided to check it out.

The caf√© is tucked away inside an industrial building, 100 Pasir Panjang, which gives it a bit of a ‚Äúhidden gem‚Äù feel. From caf√©, you get a clear view overlooking West Coast Highway, and for those driving, there‚Äôs plenty of parking available at the B1 carpark.

When we arrived, the caf√© was packed, clearly a popular spot for the holiday eve. We had to wait quite a while for a table, but the staff‚Äôs hospitality made the wait far more pleasant. The server kindly offered us the comfy sofa seats on Level 2, where we could relax, chat, before our table was available.

I opted for the set lunch menu, which was reasonably priced given the quality. I went for the Modena pizza, a thin crust, light yet flavourful sauce, and toppings that tasted fresh and organic. It was the kind of pizza that doesn‚Äôt try too hard but wins you over with its honest, wholesome flavours.

A spot worth visiting for its friendly service, comforting food, and a good dose of Italian soul. I will probably return another day during less peak hours for brunch?

title: Italian Coffee Lab Singapore
text: Pizza was delicious, but slightly not filling enough for lunch even paired with the coffee. Cheesecake made up for it as it was very dense and delicious. Loft on 2nd floor conducive for read/work on weekdays, but closes at 4pm.Moved down to 1st floor , but cleaning staff was already vacuuming and mopping even the first floor when the cafe closes at 5pm. So the whole place effectively closes at 4pm, since there was no way you can relax and continue having your drink.

title: Italian Coffee Lab Singapore
text: A big shoutout to Junear! Clumsy me spilled my cappuccino after taking just one sip. Asked a staff if he would replace it for me out of goodwill but he gave an awkward laughter but didn‚Äôt do anything about it. I bought myself another drink after that. Junear overheard the whole convo and with the ‚Äúleftover‚Äù foam from another customer‚Äôs drink, he made me another cappuccino! Junear saved the day and he deserves all the credit for being nice to a customer! A little kindness goes a long way!

title: Italian Coffee Lab Singapore
text: I love how friendly and welcoming the staffs are. had a rough week and coming here makes everything feels better. good food, atmosphere and love how hidden this place is.

title: Italian Coffee Lab Singapore
text:
We recently hosted our daughter‚Äôs birthday party at this lovely caf√©, and it was a wonderful experience from start to finish. Though it was their first time organizing a private event, caf√© owner Gus went above and beyond to make everything run smoothly.

He thoughtfully suggested that we collect pre-orders for our 60 guests, which really helped his team prepare in advance and serve the food promptly once everyone arrived. He even hired extra staff just for the day to ensure things ran efficiently.

Gus was incredibly accommodating‚Äîhe allowed the kids (ages 4 and up) to have their own space at the loft, where we held the balloon sculpting and party games. This gave them plenty of room to have fun with minimal restrictions, which we really appreciated.

The food received great feedback from our guests, and everything was served in a timely manner. Special thanks to Bob and Junear as well, who helped a lot with coordination before and during the event.

Highly recommended if you're looking for a cozy, welcoming venue for a private event!

text: Extremely disappointing experience at NUS Utown‚Äôs Udon Don Bar. I ordered a simple spicy beef rice with mentaiko fried chicken, but after more than half an hour it still wasn‚Äôt ready ‚Äî my order was #298 and they were already serving #320. The manager didn‚Äôt apologize, only kept saying ‚Äúdon is hard to make‚Äù and ‚Äúthe earlier ones were all udon‚Äù (which was clearly not true as many rice dishes came out before mine). Only after repeated urging did he ask the kitchen, ‚Äúforty minutes already,‚Äù which triggered an angry shout from the back. We responded in Chinese, and then a dark-skinned Indian man washing dishes came over, told us not to make noise, and made racially discriminatory remarks. title: CompAsia Singapore
text:
‚ö†Ô∏è WARNING TO POTENTIAL CUSTOMERS

Before you spend your money, I urge you to read the 1-star and 2-star reviews here and on Trustpilot. I now understand why so many people have complained. My experience proves that this company does not honour its warranty promises‚Äîstandard or extended. If your phone develops a fault, they will ignore you rather than repair or replace it.

I purchased an extended warranty for my Samsung S24 Ultra in good faith( Excellent condition ). When problems arose, the service I received was unacceptable:

First issue: Reported more than a week ago. No response to date.

Second issue: Reported by email. Company acknowledged it and promised a reply within 48 working hours. That deadline passed long ago‚Äîstill no update.

Previously, I removed a negative review to give them another chance. That was a mistake. The delays, silence, and lack of responsibility remain exactly the same. I have now been waiting since late July with no progress.

This is unprofessional, unethical, and a clear disregard for customers‚Äô rights. Their marketing and social media promotions are persuasive, but my experience shows these promises are empty. They have taken my hard-earned money for an extended warranty and delivered nothing in return.

I will be filing formal complaints with the relevant consumer authorities. My advice: do not waste your money here‚Äîespecially on extended warranties. You risk paying for a service they will never deliver.

title: CompAsia Singapore
text:
Utterly disappointed me for the 3rd time.

I have no choice but to deal with CompAsia because official Samsung engages with CompAsia for their trade-in services. What you see in the screenshot is what happened this year (August 2025), the driver failed to turn up after we have scheduled a pick up of my old phone on the specified date with the reason being "Car Broke Down". The date was arranged almost a month prior. This wasn't a last minute arrangement.

But this wasn't the first time this occured. In the past (2023), when I also traded-in my old phone for a new phone with Samsung, they also used CompAsia for the trade-in service and CompAsia also failed to show up the 1st time with the reason also being "Car Broke Down". We rescheduled to another date then to my shock, they told me they couldn't come again. After I got so mad at them they finally show up on the 3rd reschedule.

So what you see in the screenshot, is what just happened a few days ago (August 2025). Which means this is the 3rd time they failed to show up with the same reason, "Car Broke Down". How bad is the condition of their cars that it keeps breaking down? Everytime CompAsia has to pick up my old phone for trade -in they just couldn't make it. CompAsia doesn't understand that people had to find time and make effort to be at home and wait for them. I took a day off to be home and I'm not being paid for the day I'm not working.

Now they are telling me to reschedule and I have to risk another day of not being paid and them not showing up. They don't do pick-ups on weekends by the way. And they do this to me 3 times. Making the same mistake 3 times just seems intentional.

I don't understand why Samsung is working with them. Samsung definitely needs to know about this especially if I am not the only one experiencing this.

UPDATE : THEY DISAPPOINTED ME THE 4TH TIME
I've added additional screenshots with numbered sequence so everyone can look at the pictures in order.

1. They said to reschedule to Aug 11th, but I told them I won't be free for at least 2 weeks after they failed to show up on Aug 8th when I was ready to handover the device.

2. They still showed up Aug 11th when I wasn't home. Then tried to blame me for not being home and sent me proof of them being outside my door. But I already told them I won't be home on Aug 11th. They even acknowledged it in email that they are aware I won't be home.

What is wrong with them?

title: b88 hostel
text:
I've stayed at the b88 for 2 weeks somewhere around November '12. Was very pleasantly surprised at the quality of the digs and the services that the staff provide. The rooms are clean, well ventilated and the beds and mattresses comfortable. For me, the most important aspect were the toilets and bathrooms - these were always kept spic and span.
The staff are all young, locals, mostly studying at colleges, and consequently really know their way around town - they're really helpful and super friendly too. If you ever have a day where you don't have much to do, relax in their common area - its the ultimate way to meet new people and make some awesome friends! All in all, a really good place to stay.
This is also one of the very few places in Singapore that i know of that doesn't burn through one's holiday money simply on accommodation costs. Very reasonably priced, it is for the budget conscious (which is, i think 90% of all travelers). Singapore is no longer a rich man's holiday destination. Thank you b88! :)

title: AutoSprint
text: I sent my car in for general servicing today. Just as I was about to pick it up, I received a message from the workshop. To my surprise, Jing Wei informed me that he could arrange a slot to install my OBU today also . Since my original appointment wasn‚Äôt until 11th September 2025 due to limited availability, I was truly grateful‚Äîthis saved me from making a separate trip. The technicians completed the installation in under two hours. Thank you all for your proactive approach and swift service !

title: AutoSprint
text: My very first and last visit. While it is not ideal that timing to collect my car post serving is longer than expected, it is not a major inconvenience. Was advised to change my tyres which I did. Only to be told when I collect my car that there was a "miscommunication" between auto sprint and supplier that I have to come back another day to do my two rear tyres because they received the wrong sizes. And then was told that I need to have a newer model of tyres for my rear tyres versus what was initially quoted else they will have to remove the front ones that were ready fixed. The logic is simply flawed and does not make sense. Moreover, it meant I have to come back another day and waste more time because of the sloppiness. There is no next time and I will be replacing my rear tyres elsewhere and certainly not coming back for any servicing.

title: AutoSprint
text:
If i could give 6 stars, i would.

These guys truly live up to the Company's name. Not only was the process smooth and AUTOmated, they got the OBU installation done in less than 2 hours, almost like they were SPRINTing.

Truly appreciated them answering the 101 questions i had and accomodating my fussy-ness.  Whatsapp is manned promptly and you get replies as soon as you are dont taking a breath after typing.  Staff are extremely helpful and courteous.

If I can, i will come here to install a 100 more OBUs just to enjoy the good service. hahahahah

title: AutoSprint
text: The experiences with Auto Sprint has been great. Alvin is very responsive and took care of my issues efficiently. The car feels good driving now.

title: AutoSprint
text:
I sent my car in for the installation of the OBU. The installation process was impressively quick ‚Äî it took only one and a half hours, rather than the expected half day. Very efficient!

However, when I came to collect the car, the receptionist simply handed me the key without offering any explanation or instructions. When I asked if there was anything I needed to know, she just said, "nothing." I believe the service could be improved by providing a basic walkthrough of how to operate the OBU. It would be helpful and reassuring for customers, especially those unfamiliar with the device.

title: AutoSprint
text: Did my OBU with them. And I thought to also changed my car tyres with them same day. Upon rushing back to collect my car and having made payments for the tyre change, when told installation is ready, the OBU screen and processing unit had no lights when I started the car. I reached out and asked if they had tested it before telling me that the car is ready. They insisted that they had tested it. I had not even left Leng Kee carpark when I noticed that. Very appalled that this is the level of testing. When asked to rectify it, I was told all technicians had left for the day, and I have to return another day. I had to foot transport bills to and fro out of my pocket to compensate for their shoddy work. I had asked for compensation in the form of servicing to cover the loss incurred. The best they can do is at most 20% off their servicing through an informal text, not a servicing voucher. My only consolation was a helpful staff Abdil who tried his best to assist and escalate. For others, please watch out for situation like this.

title: Blind Massage Services
text:
If you like acupressure/ deep tissue/ tuina massage, make sure you come to this place. I had a full back (40mins) & foot reflex (60mins) for $70, the most affordable & quality massage I ever had locally. The place is simple, no frill, the focus is on the massage itself not the fancy stuff.
The masseur is professional, experienced and friendly, the pressure was perfect and all my kinks and knots smoothed out.
The place is owned and operated by the visually impaired, their professionalism and skill easily out rival any other establishment, IMO.
If you care for a chat, the team is happy to share their knowledge and experience.
To me it is not only a much needed massage, it is also a life lesson in respecting others‚Äô space and sense of self.
If you chance upon a person with limitations, ask ‚Äúhow can I help?‚Äù instead of making assumptions.

Definitely recommend to my family & friends!

title: Blind Massage Services
text:
This is one of the best massage places with an unbeatable price in SG. During the first visit, I tried the 30 min foot and 30 min shoulder combo A massage. Their skills left me so impressed that I came back a few days later for another massage. On the second visit, I tried the 60 mins non-oil body massage and it was heavenly too.

Since the 2 visits were so close to each other, the lady masseuse even remembered us as the booking name was the same. She even knew that I didn't want the massage too hard/painful so she adjusted the pressure to suit my needs. I would definitely return back to have a massage every month.

title: Blind Massage Services
text: I had a truly wonderful experience here. The massage was not only clean and professional but also incredibly comforting. The ambience was peaceful and relaxing, which made it easy to unwine. What stood out most was how attentive the therapist was! really listening to my needs and focusing on the areas that needed extra care. I left feeling refreshed, relaxed, and cared for.highly recommended!

title: Blind Massage Services
text:
I‚Äôve been coming to Blind Massage Services a few times now based on recommendations from friends, and it‚Äôs quickly become one of my go-to spots. Although the therapists may lack sight, they more than make up for it with their incredible skill, intuition, and ability to identify all my problem areas without me even having to say a word.

I especially love their foot massages ‚Äî truly some of the best I‚Äôve had! What makes the experience even better is the warm, personal touch. They greet you by name when you arrive, remembering the day‚Äôs appointments by memory alone, and check in with you during the massage to make sure everything‚Äôs comfortable. I also appreciate the little gesture of offering warm water after each session.

title: Broadway Food Centre
text:
‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê
If you‚Äôre around the area, Broadway Food Centre at Sim Lim Square is a super convenient spot to grab a quick and satisfying meal. It‚Äôs your typical food court setup with plenty of choices ‚Äî mixed veg rice, Japanese, Korean, Chinese, Malay, you name it. Really handy if you‚Äôre in Sim Lim running errands or just looking for a no-frills meal.

This time, I tried the Korean cold noodles ‚Äî and honestly, it was super refreshing. The broth was chilled and tangy, with that slight sweetness and a nice kick of spice. Noodles had a good chewy texture, and it came with sliced cucumber and egg. Perfect for a hot day! Wasn‚Äôt expecting much, but it was surprisingly satisfying.

The food came out quick too, even though the place was quite packed during lunch hour. There‚Äôs always a steady crowd, but seating turnover is fast, and it‚Äôs air-conditioned, which is a big plus.

Prices are decent, portions are generous, and there‚Äôs enough variety to suit different cravings. Definitely a good go-to if you‚Äôre nearby and want something quick, hot (or cold üòÑ), and tasty without breaking the bank.

title: Meidi-Ya Supermarket
text:
2025 June update:
The quality of the sashimi sold here has deteriorated alarmingly. It used to be fine But over the past 2 months or so, something must have changed. Yesterday's 2 trays had a mushy texture and a fishy smell. Something is wrong with the handling or the fish itself. The texture and flavour is just not that of decent (not even saying "high") quality sashimi.

2024 July update:
After visiting the Great World City outlet for a several weeks then coming back here again (because of all the NDP road closures around this side on Saturdays), I would say that the quality and quantity of things in this (Millennia Walk) branch is much better than GWC. This is particularly evident in the Sashimi. Come to this outlet to get your stuff, not the other one!

Earlier review when they 1st moved here:

Stock levels here seem to be far less predictable than when they were at Liang Court. Perhaps it's due to the smaller space, perhaps due to the COVID semi lockdown. I don't know. My frustration for today: no 1L bottle of Mirin. No Jap daikon (only Malaysia). No kawahagi. Haven't seen restock of other dried fish e.g. aji/fugu mirin boshi. Sashimi counter no longer has the tank for the occasional uni and oysters as they did previously. Koji was out of stock on our last trip but ok today.

title: Meidi-Ya Supermarket
text:
Between Isetan Scotts, Takashimaya cold storage and Meidi-Ya, I'd have to say that Meidi-Ya has the best fresh meat and fish offerings.

As a comparison, we purchased both Maguro and Salmon Belly from the various supermarkets and Meidi-Ya came out tops with deeper flavours while the others were somewhat bland.

We enjoy the beef cuts as well and can never resist going overboard, planning for yakiniku feasts over the weekends.

The wagyu beef chuck is a sure bet, beautifully marbled and assuredly soft. It only requires a 30-second sear before slinging it into your gob.

The pork jowls are also a must-have but it always needs a little seasoning to stand up to the rich flavoured cuts of beef. We even grab the yusheng from them because we trust the freshness.

I would, however, steer clear of any fruits they have on sale. They are on sale for a reason and we learnt it the hard way.

In any case, our pampered feline used to love her tiny morsels of Maguro and Sake from Meidi-Ya and just for those precious memories alone, I'll admit I'm biased and have a fondness for this supermarket. It's, after all, my furry baby's choice.

title: FUTURA BOUTIQUE HOSTEL
text:
First night in Singapore, hated it, even thought of flying directly the next day to Malaysia rather than staying in a country where accommodation are that expensive and bad at low prices.
Checkin is pretty fast using the automatic machine that delivers the badge to enter the building, no deposit if booked on Agoda directly which is nice, cash deposit is requested in other cases.
Interior is kinda modern but amenities are not convienent at all. Rooms are really small, there's no place to even open a suitcase. AC is turned all the time and is really noisy. No intimacy and worse of all is the absence of windows in the room I stayed in. Seems more like a rat cage rather than a guest house. Price was good the night I booked it so it's a plus, wouldn't stay there more than a night if no better option. Stayed at KINN following night and ngl it was wonderful... So good dormitories exist in Singapore for a decent price.

He did ask if my son ok with the waterly drink and he said ok. Sensing my frustration about the drink not being in perfect condition, he offered to pour half a cup away and allowed me to refill the other half.

text:
I had a very disappointing experience at this clinic. It was severely understaffed, with far too many patients and not enough staff to manage the flow. Despite booking the earliest slot for my medical checkup, I was made to wait for an unreasonably long time. I had been fasting for the checkup, and the delay caused me to develop gastritis from an empty stomach. The irony is astounding‚Äîpeople come here to get better, but this clinic seems to make you feel worse.

This level of inefficiency is unacceptable, especially when it affects patients‚Äô health. I hope the management takes this issue seriously and hires more staff to handle the volume of patients properly. Until then, I cannot recommend this clinic to anyone looking for timely or quality care.

text:
HIGHLY DO NOT RECOMMEND. TRY AT YOUR OWN RISK.

**Review of Jap-Kor Stall Experience**

My recent visit to the Jap-Kor stall left undesired. We ordered a bean paste soup with tofu, only to find that the tofu was sour and spoiled upon tasting. Politely informing the staff and we requested to change our order to kimchi soup, which they agreed to without additional charge, claiming it was the same price.

However, what disappointed me was the attitude of the stall attendants. When I questioned the reuse of the same soup for the kimchi soup, one of the ladies seemed indifferent, which was off-putting. Despite my request for a fresh batch of soup, the discussion became unnecessarily prolonged. The presence of the banmian auntie, who was involved in collecting money, added to the awkwardness as she defended the quality of the tofu without addressing our concerns effectively.

The continuous insistence that the tofu wasn't spoiled, accompanied by attempts to blame the bean paste, did not resolve the issue professionally. Eventually, I decided to end the conversation by asking for the soup to be returned, hinting at leaving a negative review online. This seemed to catch them off guard, resulting in an uncomfortable silence.

Overall, while the food options seemed promising, the customer service and handling of complaints at the Jap-Kor stall were disappointing.

title: Fusion Massage
text:
I have visited Fusion Spa 18 times since January 2025 and have consistently received services from the same therapist, Mandy. In my experience, she is exceptionally skilled, professional, thoughtful, and courteous. Her demeanour and expertise speak for themselves.

Contrary to a small number of negative reviews, which appear to be based on unrealistic or inappropriate expectations, Mandy‚Äôs services are of high quality and entirely professional. It is regrettable that some individuals‚Äîseemingly motivated by disappointment over not receiving unethical or non-standard services‚Äîhave left misleading or unfair reviews. These comments do not reflect the truth of the service provided.

The overwhelming majority of reviews paint an accurate and positive picture of the standards maintained by Mandy and Fusion Spa. I hope this helps provide a more balanced and fair representation for prospective clients.

title: Fusion Massage
text:
Fusion Spa Jurong :Unprofessional, Overpriced, and Unacceptable
My recent visit to Fusion Spa in Jurong was, without a doubt, the worst massage experience I've ever had. What started as a booked 1-hour Chinese massage quickly turned into a masterclass in miscommunication, aggressive upselling, and deeply unprofessional conduct.
The therapist, "Mandy" (who was far from the "overrated" service I expected), somehow converted my 1-hour session into a 30-minute oil massage ‚Äì even with a translator, I couldn't understand why this change happened. To add insult to injury, that 30-minute session was effectively only 20 minutes of actual massage time.
Her focus seemed less on therapy and more on money. She relentlessly pushed for "extra services" and tips, and when I declined, the quality of the massage noticeably plummeted. The situation became truly alarming when she attempted to pull off my underwear and explicitly solicited an "extra service" for an additional $50. I firmly refused this shocking and inappropriate offer, as I was there for a legitimate massage, nothing more.
This establishment is overpriced, employs hard-sell tactics, and the level of unprofessionalism is frankly appalling. Save your money and your peace of mind ‚Äì avoid Fusion Spa Jurong.

title: Coffee Tea Library
text:
This tea cafe is hidden inside the former Salvation Army (which is no longer operating there), which itself is located in a former primary school.

It's very Instagrammable and serves and sells a wide variety of premium specialty coffee beans and tea leaves, including Kopi Luwak (Civet Cat Coffee).

There's a seating area that has hanging swing seats and tables.

No GST or Service Charge.

It's next to the Lucky Saigon Vietnamese restaurant which itself has a forest design with a misty dry ice entrance (powered by fog machines), wooden bridge over a pond => great for romantic dinner dates. There's even a cage with fluffy Vietnamese chicken with giant feet, a food delicacy in Vietnam.

The former school's toilet condition, to be honest, is not great. It's also used by the customers of the gym/ sport businesses elsewhere in the development.

Free open-air carpark. There is a sheltered dropoff point.

For the same price you can go to literal ATLAS Bar instead of this place and receive actual service.

2. We order 9$ tea and end up with 11.90$ bill? 3 dollars of service charge FOR WHAT? for you not giving me an extra cup of tea?!

3. No alternative milk options. The person that I was with literally has lactose intolerance. What is he supposed to do with this cafe not having any options for him? Like, this is not uncommon, I think all the modern F&B business should have variety of options.

title: Coffee Tea Library
text:
Quite disappointed with the experience here. Out of the three visits I have made, I‚Äôve only managed to dine in once despite checking the opening hours prior to the journey over. Found out that this is due to the staff‚Äôs break time being unaccounted for within the operational hours listed on their establishment (or Google Maps especially for the first visit - attached picture from first visit on a Saturday, 8/6/24 12PM).

Made my way down with a friend to this place for the swing seats and cozy environment, only to be met by an unforeseen closure of an hour. When asked if we could sit and wait inside until then (as the surrounding area doesn‚Äôt have much to do and mosquitoes were flying around), we were turned away as well. I would be understanding if the break was listed like how Korean restaurants choose to take time off in the afternoon, but it‚Äôs absolutely disappointing to be turned away for something that is not accounted for within their operating hours stated. Wound up going to a different place instead.

Edit: did not check Google Maps for third visit, but I did ask staff about operational hours during my second visit + checked iG before third visit in case there were any closures not announced on Maps. I‚Äôm not sure when the break time was added into Google Maps, but don‚Äôt recall it being there during my second visit (earlier this year).

title: Coffee Tea Library
text:
If you're into tea ‚Äî like really into tea ‚Äî you‚Äôve got to check out Coffee Tea Library. This place is seriously a haven for anyone who enjoys a good cup of something warm and calming. They‚Äôve got a crazy wide selection of tea leaves from all over, and it‚Äôs not just the basic stuff. Think oolongs, rare white teas, deep earthy pu-erhs, and everything in between.

The vibe here is super chill ‚Äî kind of like a cozy book caf√© meets a modern tea shop. There are books everywhere, comfy seating, and it‚Äôs quiet enough to read, work, or just zone out with your drink.

What I loved most was how helpful the staff were. I wasn‚Äôt sure what to try, but they actually asked what kind of flavors I like and suggested a couple options I ended up loving. They do serve coffee too (which is pretty solid), and have a few snacks and pastries if you‚Äôre hungry, but honestly, the tea is what makes this place shine.

Definitely worth a visit if you‚Äôre looking for a relaxed spot to sip and chill ‚Äî or if you‚Äôre just bored of the usual caf√© scene.

title: Minmed Clinic (Redhill)
text:
I am writing to express my concern regarding the treatment my elderly mother received on 14Aug at 16:43 pm (Registration closes at 16:45)
My mother, who is in her late 70s and was unwell at the time, was told she had to reach the clinic within two minutes. I did mentioned that we are already opposite the Redhill MRT station. This expectation was highly unrealistic and did not take into account her age, physical condition, and the fact that she was experiencing vomiting/back pain.
Such requests can cause unnecessary stress to elderly patients and may even worsen their condition. I believe clinics should prioritise compassion, patience, and understanding when dealing with vulnerable patients, especially seniors.
I hope this matter can be reviewed, and that your staff will be reminded to exercise greater empathy and flexibility when handling elderly patients in the future.

title: Minmed Clinic (Redhill)
text:
Dear Minmed Team,

I would like to express my disappointment regarding an experience I had earlier today at your Redhill branch. I approached the clinic to inquire about an appointment for tomorrow, and unfortunately, I was met with unhelpful and unfriendly service (no greeting no apology) from the staff at the front desk, Shannon.

As a pregnant individual who made a special trip to the clinic seeking assistance, I expected a basic level of courtesy and support. However, Shannon did not offer a greeting, showed no willingness to accommodate my concerns, and overall made the interaction frustrating and disheartening. This lack of professionalism is especially disappointing given Minmed‚Äôs reputation for accessible and caring healthcare.

It raises the question of whether it is appropriate to have a part-timer‚Äîwho may not be fully trained in customer service or patient sensitivity‚Äîas the first point of contact in a healthcare setting.

I hope this feedback will be taken seriously and used to improve the experience for others who, like me, rely on your services during vulnerable times.

However, I believe experiences can be subjective, and in my case, I was fortunate to be attended to by Shwu En, who greeted me warmly with a smile and made the entire process smooth and stress-free. She took care of everything‚Äîfrom registration to making sure I was covered under insurance, all the way through to the consultation and arranging for the ultrasound (which I had to do at a hospital later). title: iStudio One Holland Village
text:
I remember visiting the store during last year‚Äôs New Year. At the time, I was frustrated and unsure how to deal with my phone issue. I‚Äôm really glad I met the staff member, Pin, who quickly identified that the problem was caused by other factors affecting the phone.

I also couldn‚Äôt decide between product A and B, and he gave me very practical advice! Later on, I returned to the store to make the purchase, and I was very satisfied with my choice‚Äîthanks to Pin‚Äôs help and suggestions!

I‚Äôve been to several other, even larger, Apple stores before, but I‚Äôve never met a staff member as knowledgeable, attentive, and helpful about Apple products as Pin. I feel truly fortunate to have met him at this branch.

Just last week, I experienced another issue with my phone and made a point to return to the same store. Pin happened to be there again, and as always, he patiently helped me understand the issue so I could try to resolve it before deciding on the next step.

I sincerely hope that all Apple stores will have staff members like Pin‚Äîknowledgeable, warm, and detail-oriented. It would definitely make customers feel more at ease and ensure a long-term, trustworthy, and enjoyable shopping experience!

text: First of all the room (room 215) is way smaller than in the pictures on agoda. The bathroom is very tight, the shower is in between a wall and the toilet making it very uncomfortable to take a shower, and the shower handle is wobbly making it impossible to adjust the water temperature (there‚Äôs no cold water). Second of all as we were inspecting the bed we noticed black spots on the bedsheets, and the following hour we found a red/black insect on the bed. The day after we noticed that they were many bugs (BED BUGS) and even more black spots (bed bugs remains) meaning that there‚Äôs a untreated infestation. We alerted the staff and they told us that it was the first time that something like this had happened but after further analysis we noticed that they were many complains about bed bugs in the past month (July). I find it very unsanitary that they made us change rooms while maybe transporting the bed bugs with us. We didn‚Äôt even get a refund for the inconvenience even if we did pay about 135$ per night. title: Butternut Tree Hotel
text:
This hotel is absolutely worth recommending, and here‚Äôs why:

Location: 3/5
Cleanliness: 4/5
Service Attitude: 5/5
Value for Money: 5/5

I managed to book this hotel at a super affordable promotional rate! To my surprise, the price included a private bathroom ‚Äî and even room cleaning service, which was unexpected! What impressed me the most was the front desk staff‚Äôs service ‚Äî they were extremely polite and greeted us with a cheerful ‚ÄúGood morning‚Äù every day as we left the hotel.

There‚Äôs also a bar in the hotel, perfect for relaxing after a long day out. Plus, the hotel provides a public drinking water dispenser ‚Äî I really appreciated that!

The only downside is that it takes about a 10-minute walk to the nearest MRT station. However, for those who take the bus, the bus stop is very close by. The room isn‚Äôt particularly big, but for RM200 a night, I dare you to compare ‚Äî you won‚Äôt easily find another hotel offering a private bathroom and a double bed at this price.

I honestly don‚Äôt understand why some people are complaining. If I hadn‚Äôt stayed here myself, I might have believed those negative reviews ‚Äî and almost missed out on this gem!

title: Butternut Tree Hotel
text:
This was our second time staying at Butternut, and we didn‚Äôt even consider looking at other hotels because our first stay left such a positive impression. Most of the staff were still as warm, friendly, and welcoming as we remembered, and we truly appreciated that. However, this recent stay felt quite different from our first.

Previously, we booked the L Room with Queen Bed and Window (12 m¬≤/129 ft¬≤), which felt spacious and comfortable. We had two large suitcases, two small ones, and two personal bags--and we could easily lay both large suitcases open on the floor with slight room to move around. This time, we chose the L Room with Skylight Window, which is also listed as 12 m¬≤/129 ft¬≤ on Agoda. However, the layout felt SIGNIFICANTLY more cramped than expected. I cannot stress SIGNIFICANTLY enough. We could only open one suitcase at a time, and with limited floor space, it was difficult to move around...especially after shopping or with larger luggage. The room appeared more spacious in the photos, but in person, it felt closer in size to an M or even an S room. Although the listed area is the same as our previous room, the difference in usable space was quite noticeable, and honestly, it was our biggest letdown during this stay.

We also noticed that some of the amenities listed for our room like slippers, a desk, a telephone, and an in-room or laptop safe were not available. My partner kindly asked the front desk for slippers, but we were told they were unavailable. We're not sure if this was a temporary situation or if these items are no longer part of the standard setup.

Another thing to keep in mind is that there‚Äôs no lift access to the 4th floor. You have to take the stairs. This might be important to consider for guests with heavy or bulky luggage and might get a room at the 4th floor. Also, the air conditioning took quite some time (around two hours) to cool the room, which was a bit surprising given its compact size.

We do hope the property stays true to what is described and promised in their listing in the future. We were honestly disappointed by the discrepancies, especially after having such a great first stay last 2023. While we did encounter one staff member who seemed a bit unfriendly, we truly appreciate the rest of the team who were consistently kind, accommodating, and approachable throughout our stay. Their warm hospitality is one of the reasons we might still consider staying at Butternut again...along with its convenient location near Maxwell Food Centre, Maxwell MRT, and Chinatown Complex.

title: COURTS Orchard
text:
Visited Courts Nojima on 3 August to explore buying a dryer. Did not expect it to be the start of many troubles.

Was wrongly advised by sales staff regarding the SG60 discounts ($120 off instead of $60) and use of climate vouchers for a dryer (cannot be used) only at the point of purchase. Decided to proceed with buying the Samsung dryer.

After purchase, did not receive any confirmation of notification of delivery of actual date, only a call 10 mins before delivery. Delivery window was 10am to 2pm, and ended up staying home for 3 hours (10am to 1pm) before getting a call that the delivery was coming. Sales staff also was hard to contact regarding delivery (2 to 3h wait, only responded after calling). Understand it was his off day, but Courts should have a staff to cover for him since it still involved deliveries, or have a more contactable number.

Sales staff also wrongly scheduled the Samsung delivery agent, so ended up the agent only came 1 day after the dryer was delivered. Asked for a specific time for the agent to come (3pm) to make up for the mistake but ended up with delaying my delivery window (originally 2 to 6pm) to 3 to 7pm. As of 545pm, the agent is still not here. (Edit: Agent ended up being late, and I was forced to take cab to my appointment)

This is one of my worst sales service to date, from pre to post sales. The only good things about this whole process was the advice given on the right dryer to buy (pre sales) and the free delivery given in an attempt to recover from the mistake in the supposed discount.

Please work on your service processes and sales recovery. It is alarming how poor the standards are.

title: COURTS Orchard
text:
Staff are not very helpful and not knowledgeable about their products and offerings. Even small 7eleven store cashiers are better than these lazy staff.

I bought a camera here that will be used as a gift. No one was around to help, so I went to the cashier area and asked someone to sell the item to me. I specifically asked if the item I will be buying can be returned as I don't want to open the box since it will be a gift I will give on my overseas trip. The guy who helped me said it could be returned after 14 days. I counted my overseas trip days, and if ever there is a defect, I can still return it after my trip.

Armed with this info, I immediately paid for the item. When I double-checked with the cashier about the return policy, much to my surprise, he said the item only has a 1 week return policy. I argued that they falsely provided sales terms and misled me into buying the item. As a compromise, I asked if they could test it instead, though I am hesitant since I want the box sealed when I give my gift - but to add to the incompetence so far, they said they don't have a dedicated salesperson who can test it.

Since they have no solutions for me and we just stared at each other for minutes with no one offering even a simple apology, much less a work around the issue, I just opted to refund the item.

When the person who will process my refund came and asked the guy if I would need a refund, the guy even had the gall to tell her I changed my mind. I didn't let it pass since they are the one who changed the terms of sale right there, not me. Stores usually get sued and fined for this kind of misleading sales, but the staff are not even bothered by the mistake and incompetence they just displayed. In any other setup, this kind of attitude leads to suspension or even dismissal, but I guess Courts Orchard management is satisfied with being mediocre and incompetent.

title: Central 24-Hr Clinic (Clementi) - CHAS | GP Clinic | 24 Â∞èÊó∂ ËØäÊâÄ
text:
I visited this clinic in the hope of avoiding a trip to the A&E, but the experience turned out to be one of the most appalling I‚Äôve ever encountered in a healthcare setting.

Before arriving, my husband called ahead to explain that I was in severe pain and to check if the clinic could assist. The receptionist who answered was shockingly rude ‚Äî no greeting, no courtesy, just a blunt ‚ÄúWhat do you want?‚Äù That should have been the first red flag, but we held on to hope that once there, we would receive proper medical attention.

When we arrived and I informed the same receptionist that I was in intense pain, she didn‚Äôt even look up or acknowledge me with any concern. Instead, she continued chatting with another patient about billing instructions. Only after that did she turn to me ‚Äî not to direct me to the doctor, but to insist on registering my IC and taking down my particulars. This, despite my repeated pleas and visible distress.

I had to reason with her ‚Äî that surely I could be seen by the doctor first and the administrative steps could wait until I was stable. Her lack of urgency and basic empathy was both disturbing and unacceptable.

But what truly shocked me was the doctor‚Äôs response. After a brief glance, he immediately said, ‚ÄúI can‚Äôt help you, you need to go to A&E.‚Äù There was no attempt to assess, no first-aid measures, no questions ‚Äî just a quick dismissal. And to make matters worse, he criticised me for being agitated due to the pain, telling me I shouldn‚Äôt behave that way. I cannot understand how a medical professional could lack such fundamental compassion and empathy. No help rendered. Continued sitting at his chair.

This entire experience was deeply traumatic, not just because of the pain I was in, but because of how dehumanising the encounter felt. There was zero empathy, zero professionalism ‚Äî from the receptionist to the doctor.

If this is how you treat patients in distress, you have no place in the healthcare profession. I strongly advise others to avoid this clinic at all costs. It is simply unacceptable.

The only saving grace was one young staff who helped to call the ambulance. Thank you for your kind help.

For the corporate office: this incident occurred on Saturday, 26 July, at approximately 3:00PM. Please investigate accordingly. The staff and doctor on duty should be held accountable.

title: ValueMax Pawnshop & Jewellery (People's Park Centre Branch)
text:
Located in an older mall, People's Park Centre, this location of the ValueMax chain had good service and a good inventory for their size.

Buys and sells gold jewelry by the gram, with a percentage cut below or above the price of gold, respectively. Combination of new and secondhand pieces available. Secondhand pieces don't have VAT tax (7%) or a workmanship fee (~7-8?%), new pieces do.

They prefer cash, atm card, or NETS. They'll charge 3% for a CC, including foreign (VISA, MC) debit card. There is some wiggle room; in my purchase I couldn't withdraw enough cash due to a foreign atm limit and didn't want to pay the cc surcharge. I was going to come back the next day, but they got manager override to waive the cc fee.

title: Images of Singapore
text:
The Spirit of Singapore Boat Ride at Sentosa's Madame Tussauds is a attractive experience that takes you on a journey through Singapore's rich cultural tapestry. The ride showcases key landmarks and cultural elements by immersive effects and informative narration. The overall enjoyment may depend on personal interest in cultural experiences and educational value rather than thrilling rides.

Images of Singapore is an educational attraction located within Sentosa's Madame Tussauds. Visitors are treated to interactive exhibits, lifelike displays, and multimedia presentations. The attraction is well-curated, providing insights into Singapore. Images of Singapore offers a comprehensive overview in an engaging format.

Some visitors may find it more informative than thrilling. The attention to detail and the quality of presentation make it a valuable experience. It's particularly suitable for families and tourists looking to delve deeper into the local heritage.

title: RedDoorz Plus Near Gold Coast Ferry Terminal Batam
text:
Very old and tired rooms. BUT the staff, service and location are all great. Big shout out to Alif and Deena. Their service is warm, friendly and professional. Better service than many 4 star hotels.

I also like that each floor (including the lobby / reception area) has large "public spaces" with sofas üõãÔ∏è, chairs and coffee tables to lounge at, chill out and grab a snack. That's quite unusual.

You do get the feeling that with some investment, this could be a great little boutique hotel in the Bengkong Laut / Golden City area. The other two hotels (Golden Bay and Golden View) are also pretty old, tired and in desperate need of renovation. Golden View Hotel is also MASSIVELY overpriced.

I'd really like to see this hotel be renovated. The area needs more, good, accommodation because there's a lot to see and do in the area - beaches, beach clubs, historic mosque (Masjid Cheng Hoo), many fantastic eateries, watersports, Wake Park, theme parks, carousel üé†, üé° wheel, food and drink stalls, miniature houses open museum, go kart üèéÔ∏è track etc etc etc.

In Bahasa >

Kamarnya sangat tua dan usang. TAPI staf, layanan, dan lokasinya luar biasa. Salut untuk Alif dan Deena. Layanan mereka hangat, ramah, dan profesional. Layanannya lebih baik daripada kebanyakan hotel bintang 4.

Saya juga suka bahwa setiap lantai (termasuk lobi/area resepsionis) memiliki "ruang publik" yang luas dengan sofa üõãÔ∏è, kursi, dan meja kopi untuk bersantai, bersantai, dan menikmati camilan. Hal yang cukup unik.

Anda mungkin merasa bahwa dengan sedikit investasi, ini bisa menjadi hotel butik kecil yang bagus di area Bengkong Laut/Golden City. Dua hotel lainnya (Golden Bay dan Golden View) juga cukup tua, usang, dan sangat membutuhkan renovasi. Golden View Hotel juga SANGAT mahal.

Saya sangat ingin melihat hotel ini direnovasi.  Daerah ini butuh lebih banyak akomodasi yang bagus, karena ada banyak hal yang bisa dilihat dan dilakukan di daerah tersebut - pantai, klub pantai, masjid bersejarah (Masjid Cheng Hoo), banyak tempat makan yang fantastis, olahraga air, Wake Park, taman hiburan, komidi putar üé†, bianglala üé°, kios makanan dan minuman, rumah miniatur museum terbuka, lintasan go kart üèéÔ∏è, dll.

1st August Thursday around 9pm plus, my friend and I went to buy food at 7/11 because we were hungry and we knew alot of shops were closing at this timing. While we were choosing food, I saw that the kimchi cup noodles was on discount 1 for 1 so I encouraged my friend to get one with me even though he already planned to get another food item.. as we paid our food together at the counter, i initially didn't calculate the prices properly but after eating I realised that $14plus for 2 cup noodles (which is supposed to be the price of one $3.20) and one chicken wrap $3.80 and one chicken breast $3.10 does not add up to $14 sth which was what she charged us for.. it was supposed to be $10.10 only.

When i went back to tell her and ask her about the price she charged, I realised that all the discount tags that were there were all taken down.. and when I told her I saw it while I was buying she said the discount doesn't exist. Another worker was there and he said that the discounts we saw were expired discounts so it no longer applies. I told them that it's not my fault that they forgot to remove expired discounts and should not have overcharged us for it and not do anything about it but argue back. Now I feel so bad for encouraging my friend to buy the cup noodle when he initially didn't even want to eat it. This lady was so uncooperative and unapologetic so I just left angrily without being compensated whatsoever.
I hope the 7/11 managers can remind their staff to remove discounts on time and be accountable for their mistakes. As a student who has very limited budget, 7/11 food is already very pricey for me and now with this overcharging I feel very very frustrated and angry about this unpleasant incident.

title: My Car Auto Workshop Singapore | Carworkshop.com.sg
text: My car Malfunction Warning Indicator Light started blinking on Valentine's Day, Wednesday, (5th Day of the Lunar New Year). Did some research on the internet and found some workshops with positive reviews. However, Mincent Car Workshop Singapore was the only workshop with 5 Stars rating and all positive reviews. Tried calling them and other's positive reviews workshop on Thursday, however they were closed. Finally contacted Mincent on Friday and spoke with the boss's Junyang that I will dropped by his workshop in the afternoon after 2pm. My car was vibrating violently both when idling and driving, checked my car's manual and it could be my Electronic Control Unit (ECU) issues. Asked him if my car should be tow to his workshop or I am still able to drive there. He advised driving slowly to the workshop and if there are any problems, I can contact him immediately. Managed to reached his workshop at about 3.30pm. As it is still CNY's holidays, his workshop has only 1 mechanic, otherwise he would have 3 to 4 mechanics. His partner in business spoke to me when I arrived there, and directly me to Junyang. Both him and his partner are customer's oriented persons and very sociable. They will interact with customers and explain clearly the problems with their cars and what needed to be done and the cost of the repairs before proceeding with the repairs. They price is very reasonable. As they do not store a lot of spare parts in their small workshop, they have to ordered from their regular suppliers. Despite that, they are able to diagnosed my car's problems within 30 minutes (4pm). Luckily the problems were my spark plugs and ignition coils, and not my ECU. I agreed on the cost of the repairs and I drove my car home at 5 plus, despite there were many customers at his workshop. His mechanic is very skilled, knowledgeable and friendly as well. Thank you Junyang and his team at Mincent! I will return there if I need to do regular maintenances and other car services in the future! I will definitely recommend Mincent to my friends and colleagues!

title: Jimmy Monkey Cafe & Bar
text:
Visited Jimmy Monkey at PLQ for a casual dinner gathering, as we were looking for a kid-friendly spot.

We were seated at an outdoor table conveniently located right next to the playground, which was great for families with young children. However, do note that the outdoor area had some mosquitoes, so insect repellent might come in handy.

We ordered a variety of dishes to share ‚Äì the salmon steak, wagyu burger, white clams in white sauce, aglio olio with prawns, cornflake chicken breast, and the sweet & sour cauliflower. They also offer a kids‚Äô menu, which includes a main and drink ‚Äì a thoughtful touch for families.

Unfortunately, while the food was decent, the service left much to be desired. It appeared that only one service staff was managing the floor, which resulted in a long wait for drinks and multiple reminders needed for cutlery, condiments, and basic requests.

Overall, the experience was underwhelming, and while the location is great for families, we‚Äôre unlikely to return given the slow service.

üü¢ Nestled away in the verdant & lush vicinity of One-North Residences, Jimmy Monkey Cafe is a hidden gem delight that blends laid-back charm with a casual cafe culture vibe.

üü¶  The cafe is situated at the foot of a block of low-rise condominium residences.

‚ú≥Ô∏è This small cafe offers a tranquil escape that feels far removed from the city‚Äôs buzz‚Äîyet it remains accessible.‚úîÔ∏è The cafe is just a short walk from One-North MRT station.

‚ö´Ô∏è The decor is industrial-chic style ‚Äî think exposed brick, polished concrete, and warm wood tones offset by eclectic vintage accents.

üîµ Service here is friendly & casual. The staff here strikes a fine balance between pleasant hospitality and efficient operation.

üü†  The cafe latte here is smooth and rich with a full-bodied espresso base‚Äîclearly well crafted.  ‚ñ™Ô∏é Coffee is served from an exclusive hand-crafted Slayer Machine.

üü´ The grilled cheese sandwich was hearty and satisfying, served warm with just the right crunch. It‚Äôs comfort food done well.

üü® The scone had a rustic homemade quality‚Äîgreat with a pat of butter & jam and a sip of that good coffee. My hubby and I shared the food.

üî∑Ô∏è On weekdays, this is a serene space that invites you to slow down, relax, and enjoy the moment. It's quiet here and I've been here several times over the years since 2013, because one of my cousins lives in this area.

text:
This North bridge road market and food centre is seldom mentioned and overlooked if compared to Goldenmile Food Centre .
Recently refurbished it is now brighter and cleaner.

title: North Bridge Road Market & Food Centre
text: This is a relatively recent refurbishment and is one of the cleanest hawker centers you will come across in Singapore. It is very well ventilated with a few of those long bladed low velocity high volume fans. Next the food‚Ä¶ the fish ball noodle shop is open 24hrs ‚Ä¶ it is excellent. Noodles are al dente and the fish balls are nice. The lor mee is similarly excellent. Can‚Äôt say the same about the prawn noodle shop though. It sells prawn noodles, pork rib noodles, wonton noodles, and some combination of chicken and charsiew rice. The noodles are pedestrian and the meats are not very good. The pork rib noodle is tasty but that‚Äôs the noodle. The meat itself is not very tasty and not very soft. Ditto the charsiew. Also very strange for pork rib noodles to be served on a plate. It‚Äôs just weird. I‚Äôd avoid this stall like the plague the next time. I see a very enticing fish porridge soup. Oh and I like the soya bean stall. There are others but not all are open even on a Saturday (or because it is a Saturday‚Ä¶ been 3 Saturdays). If visiting, please avoid parking there for Saturday lunch. It took us over 30 mins to get out of the carpark ‚Ä¶ perhaps because the people going to ICA are parking here and it‚Äôs a really bad layout. It felt like waiting in a JB jam. If I crawled, I would have left the carpark in 10 minutes.

title: Central Square Canteen
text:
It is a smaller canteen, compared to Frontier, Deck, or Technoedge. It has several stalls ‚Äî Thai, Mala, Mixed Vegetable Rice, Ban Mian/Fish Soup, and Indian (Vegetarian).

For the Thai food:
1. The green curry chicken is good, but quite spicy. The chicken slices are quite plenty.
2. The pandan chicken is also good -- it is well-marinated and juicy.

For the Ban Mian/Fish soup stall:
1. The double fish soup is good. You can opt for milk to be put in as well. 2. The dumplings are also good. It is filled with a mixture of chives and pork and is juicy.
3. The tomato egg noodle is good too. It is like ban mian, except that the soup base is sweet and slightly tangy.

For the La Mian/Hotplate stall, they have beef noodle. The beef slices are tender, but maybe, the spicy option would be better, as the non-spicy option made the soup tasted salty.

For the Waffles stall, they have the waffle with ice cream. The waffle itself is crispy. The ice cream flavors are also quite good -- I particularly liked the cookies and cream and the mango.

title: BEAT. Capsule Hostel @ Boat Quay
text: BEAT. Capsules has a fantastic location right in the heart of Boat Quay, surrounded by vibrant shops and restaurants with easy access to Singapore‚Äôs key attractions. The view of the river is stunning, especially at night. However, some guests can be a bit noisy, which might disturb light sleepers. Overall, a great budget stay with a prime spot!

title: The Warehouse Lobby Bar (Robertson Quay)
text: I was visiting Singapore and on the search for the best cocktail bars. A friend of mine told me I needed to visit here. I am so glad I did! Jay and Ralph at the bar were top tier! Not only did they make some delicious cocktails, but they were engaging, insanely knowledgeable and we had great conversations. The bar atmosphere is top tier and unlike anything I saw during my time in Singapore. Definitely find the time to come visit this gem!

title: The Warehouse Lobby Bar (Robertson Quay)
text:
We visited the Lobby Bar at The Warehouse Hotel on 17 April 2025, and naturally the ambience of the hotel was unparalleled, but the highlight of our evening was Randid. From the moment we arrived, he made us feel welcome and served us delicious passionfruit-infused welcome drinks that had us craving for more.

Randid also took the time to introduce to us some truly unusual spirits, including a memorable mala-infused creation that made me (just me!) want to have Haidilao.

We will be back for more! Thanks again Randid!

text:
üåø‚¨õÔ∏è The Warehouse Lobby Bar
üüß The Warehouse Hotel
320 Havelock Road
Singapore 169628

üü´  The Warehouse Lobby Bar at the Warehouse Hotel at Havelock Road is a stylish and industrial-chic bar that serves up craft cocktails in a unique and atmospheric setting.

üüßThe lobby bar is situated in a beautifully restored 19th-century warehouse (built in 1895), with exposed brick walls, high ceilings, and polished concrete floors. The decor is modern and sleek, with comfortable & plush sofa seating areas and a lively bar counter.

üîµ The drink menu is creative and extensive, with a focus on handcrafted cocktails. The bar also serves a selection of wine, beer, and champagne.

üü® We ordered 2 cups of Hot Cafe Latte and were served by Isabelle, a very polite, nice and cheerful lady.ü©∑ Because of Isabelle's great & empathetic attitude, I am giving the Warehouse Lobby Bar 5 stars.

‚¨õÔ∏è Overall, the Warehouse Lobby Bar is a great spot to relax and unwind with friends or family, and take in the stylish and historic surroundings.

üåøüîµ Dated 15th Feb 2025 Sat at approx 8pm.

title: Baden Restaurant & Pub
text:
As a Holland Village pub it could do far worse, but as a purveyor of classic Bavarian fare it's no match for even Brotzeit, yet alone the nearby Huber's or the now-dead Frieda.

That said, the fact that they open and serve food till fairly late (10+ pm) is a great plus in their book, and service is friendly and fairly prompt, though to be fair the place was pretty empty on a Sunday night.

Decent variety of your run of the mill witbiers, though their relatively more special in-house brew, the Helles, was out the night we visited

Ok:
- Sausage platter. Sausages were okay, if a little salty and not really having enough bite. Mash was way too runny. Sauerkraut out of a jar. Honestly, for a repast that's available this late at night I can't fault them overly much for the TV-dinner quality of food on hand.

title: Baden Restaurant & Pub
text:
If you‚Äôre looking for an authentic slice of Germany right in the heart of Holland Village, Baden Restaurant & Pub is the place to be! The moment you step in, you‚Äôre greeted with warm, rustic charm and a lively, welcoming atmosphere that makes you feel right at home.

The food is absolutely top-notch ‚Äì hearty, flavorful, and made with love. The pork knuckle is hands down one of the best in Singapore: crispy on the outside, tender on the inside, and served with rich, savory gravy. Pair it with their signature sausages and a cold German beer, and you‚Äôve got the perfect meal.

The staff are friendly, attentive, and genuinely passionate about what they do. Service is prompt even during peak hours, and they‚Äôre always happy to offer recommendations if you‚Äôre unsure what to try.

Whether you‚Äôre here for a relaxed dinner, a round of beers with friends, or just to soak in the vibes, Baden never disappoints. It‚Äôs a rare gem that keeps you coming back for more!

Highly recommend ‚Äì 5 stars all the way!

title: Baden Restaurant & Pub
text: Baden Restaurant and Pub is an absolute gem! The atmosphere is warm and welcoming, perfect for both casual nights out and special occasions. The food is consistently delicious‚Äîespecially the Pork Knuckle, which are juicy and full of flavor. Their drink selection is great too, with a nice variety of local beers on tap. The staff is friendly, attentive, and really make you feel at home. I highly recommend this place to anyone looking for great food, great service, and a great time!

title: Baden Restaurant & Pub
text:
Baden Restaurant & Pub is an absolute gem in the heart of Holland Village! From the moment you step in, the cozy, rustic German pub vibe sets the tone for a warm and welcoming dining experience. Whether you're here for dinner or late-night drinks, Baden delivers consistently.

The food is a standout ‚Äî the pork knuckle is perfectly crispy on the outside and juicy inside, a true crowd-pleaser. Their sausages are rich, flavorful, and authentically German, and the sides like sauerkraut and mashed potatoes round out the meal beautifully. Pair all that with an ice-cold pint from their solid beer selection, and you‚Äôve got the perfect combo.

Service is friendly and attentive, even when the place is buzzing. The staff are always quick to offer recommendations and make you feel right at home.

Whether you're a regular or it's your first time, Baden makes you feel like you're part of the family. Great food, great drinks, great vibes ‚Äî can‚Äôt recommend it enough!

title: Baden Restaurant & Pub
text:
I chose Baden Restaurant & Pub to celebrate my birthday, expecting a wonderful experience based on its reputation. Unfortunately, the evening turned out to be deeply disappointing due to the unprofessional handling of an uncomfortable situation.

The evening started well, with swift service and a pleasant outdoor setup. However, the experience took a turn when a guest seated beside us, who appeared intoxicated, took my steak knife and began touching my food. Shocked, I brought this to the attention of the waiter, expecting it to be resolved appropriately. Instead, I was met with dismissiveness and unprofessional behavior.

The waiter told me, ‚ÄúCome on lah, bro, this is my regular customer, I‚Äôll take care of it,‚Äù while patting me on the shoulder. When I politely asked him not to touch me, his behavior escalated as he yelled at me in Malay, using inappropriate language. Despite informing the manager, no meaningful resolution was offered. The manager insisted that I stay, despite my clear discomfort, and ignored my request to settle the bill promptly.

Eventually, I left the restaurant without tasting any of the food I had ordered. This experience not only ruined my birthday celebration but left me feeling disrespected as a customer.

I hope the management addresses these issues seriously to ensure other patrons do not endure similar treatment.

title: Senja Hawker Centre
text: Senja Hawker Centre is a huge hawker centre with very, very high ceiling. It is still reasonable cool even in a very hot day as there are mounted massive fans to circulate the air. Although the place can house hundreds of people, noise level is still reasonable for families and friends to have good conversations because of the high ceiling and the spaciousness of the place. In terms of food, it is excellent due to its variety, quality and affordability. You have a cai peng stall with lots of food dishes and a Michelin star zhi char stall with good customer service. You can order a set meal of 3 claypot dishes with delicious tastes. There are many, many other good stalls. Overall, you can get good amount of food quantity for the price that you paid. Enjoy your visit to the Senja Hawker Centre!

title: Quick Lane SG Car Care, Parts & Accessories
text:
‚≠ê 1 Star (if I could give 0, I would)

I‚Äôve been servicing my car with Quicklane for over 9 years because they always push me into buying their servicing packages ‚Äî which ties me down to them. In the early years, before they onboarded BYD, their servicing standards were excellent and I was genuinely happy, which is why I kept buying their packages. But even with a package, I always seemed to incur extra charges here and there.

Since they started handling BYD, everything has gone downhill. The CSAs don‚Äôt bother replying to messages, and when they finally do, the service attitude is shockingly poor.

My most recent experience was the last straw:
‚Ä¢	After sending my car in for servicing, I had to tow it off the highway just 2 days later.
‚Ä¢	When they couldn‚Äôt identify the issue, their ‚Äúsolution‚Äù was simply to replace parts at my cost. Convenient, isn‚Äôt it?
‚Ä¢	My Bluetooth system issue has dragged on forever ‚Äî their answer? Replace the entire radio system! What nonsense.
‚Ä¢	Within the SAME month of servicing, my engine light came on. When I asked why this happened right after servicing, they had no proper explanation and instead told me to come down for a diagnostic test ‚Äî and pay another $70 for it.

Before sending the car in, I never had these issues. Now I‚Äôm left with even more problems, extra bills, and no accountability from them.
