title: Quick Lane SG Car Care, Parts & Accessories
text:
My Commendation for the Outstanding Service to the customer service advisor Mr. Mohamed Nasir

I am writing to express my deepest appreciation for the exceptional service provided by Mr. Nasir from Quick Lane who serves at Sime Darby / Vantage Automotive Ltd at Alexandra .

On 21st July 2025 at 4:30 PM , my car broke down in my estate carpark. In this stressful situation, I contacted Mr. Nasir, who responded promptly and patiently .He expertly guided me through identifying potential causes of the breakdown, demonstrating remarkable knowledge and professionalism. His calm and reassuring approach immediately gave me peace of mind.

My vehicle was towed to the Quick Lane workshop at Alexandra, where Mr. Nasir continued to provide outstanding support. He kept me informed throughout the diagnostic process and promptly explained the issue of my car failure was due to the gear lever cable assembly had failed, preventing the engine from starting.

Despite the workshop being exceptionally busy with numerous maintenance services , Mr. Nasir coordinate very well with his technical team and repaired my car efficiently, replacing the new gear lever cable assembly and my car was tested ok . He also proactively followed up on my car scheduled routine service, ensuring I was reminded and well-informed.

Mr. Nasir‚Äôs expertise, dedication, and customer-centric attitude truly exceeded my expectations. I am thoroughly delighted with his excellent service.

I believed Mr. Nasir for his excellence , he embodies the highest standards of Quick Lane commitment to customer care.

Mr. Nasir , I thank you for fostering such a professional and reliable service environment . Keep it up and well done üëçüôè

title: Fort Siloso
text: This historical exhibition facility on Sentosa Island tells the story of wars in Southeast Asia(Especially in Singapore). The explanations are written in three languages: English, Chinese, and Japanese, making it easy to understand. The exhibits are not simply books on the history of the time, but also include photographs, the war situation in each country, and life-size wax figures of wartime meetings. The entire exhibit is packed with information, so we recommend taking your time to explore(at least 2H). It's easy to climb the mountain toward the fort to see the exhibits, and then walk along the Siloso Skywalk on your way back.

text:
The Bukit Timah Temporary Market, set up in October 2024 to house displaced hawkers from the original Bukit Timah Market and Food Centre, continues to deliver on what matters most: food that‚Äôs rooted in tradition and flavor.

During a recent visit, the highlight was a plate of Hokkien Mee, which retained the wok hei aroma and balanced seafood richness that fans of the original centre would recognize. The noodles were well-braised, with a generous mix of prawns and squid, and came with a sambal that was both smoky and sharp. Despite the change in location, the quality and character of the dish remain impressively intact.

For dessert, the Ice Kachang offered a refreshing counterpoint. It came tall and finely shaved, with a classic mix of red beans, attap seeds, jelly, and sweet corn, topped with syrup that didn‚Äôt overwhelm. The texture and taste were reminiscent of hawker desserts from an earlier era ‚Äî unpretentious and satisfying.

While the market can feel stuffy, especially during lunchtime, this is an understandable trade-off given its temporary structure and heavy foot traffic. Ventilation fans are in place, but visitors might prefer to come earlier in the day or later in the afternoon for a more comfortable experience.

Despite the spatial limitations, the market maintains a familiar charm. Seating is reasonably ample, the place is kept clean, and stallholders continue to serve food with the same energy and pride as before. For those who frequented the old Bukit Timah Market, the new setup offers continuity ‚Äî not just in taste, but in spirit.

For anyone looking to revisit old favourites or explore enduring hawker craft, the Jalan Seh Chuan site is well worth the trip.

title: Alexandra Arch Overhead Bridge
text:
Alexandra Arch is a unique and beautifully designed pedestrian bridge that‚Äôs perfect for nature lovers and photography enthusiasts. Its modern architecture, with a sleek curved design, stands out against the surrounding greenery.

The bridge connects seamlessly to the Southern Ridges trail, making it a great starting point for a scenic walk through lush parks and forests. The views from the bridge are lovely, especially in the evening when it‚Äôs illuminated with colorful LED lights.

While the area can get a bit warm during the day, the cool breeze and shaded sections along the trail make the walk enjoyable. It‚Äôs also relatively quiet, offering a peaceful escape from the city‚Äôs hustle and bustle.

Whether you‚Äôre hiking the Southern Ridges or just exploring Singapore‚Äôs green spaces, Alexandra Arch is a must-visit spot. A great place to enjoy nature and snap some Instagram-worthy photos!

text:
I had an absolutely amazing stay during my time in Singapore. The host was incredibly welcoming, helpful, and genuinely friendly, The pod setup is not only super comfy but also gives off a very modern, futuristic vibe, perfect for a unique and cozy experience.

One of the highlights was the complimentary breakfast each morning, which was a great way to start the day. On top of that, having access to coffee and tea 24/7 was a thoughtful touch that I really appreciated. And the location is also in walking distance to MRT and Bus stop.

Everything was clean, comfortable, and well-organized. It‚Äôs clear that a lot of care goes into making guests feel comfortable and taken care of. I would highly recommend this place to anyone visiting Singapore, and I‚Äôll definitely be coming back on my next trip!

title: Spacepod@lavender
text:
I stayed 5 nights at this hostel, which uses capsule-style beds for sleeping. Overall, the experience was very pleasant, although there are a few aspects to consider.

ROOM:
The capsules do not have doors, so much like in a typical hostel, you can hear everything happening around you. Additionally, the capsule structure is quite noisy; any movement causes creaking sounds that could disturb your roommates.

That said, the setup was otherwise great. Each capsule includes a power outlet, RGB lighting, a fan system, and the room has air conditioning.

SERVICE:
The service was excellent.
The staff were friendly and quick to respond to requests. We asked for an extra blanket and a fresh towel, and both were provided promptly.

Breakfast is included, though it‚Äôs simple: toasted bread with butter, chocolate spread, or peanut butter. Tea and coffee are available 24/7, which is a nice touch.

LOCATION:
The location is ideal for exploring the city. The metro station is just a 5-minute walk away, and both Little India and Chinatown can be reached on foot within a short time.

title: Bar Intermezzo
text:
Step into a world where tradition meets indulgence and be impressed with the variety of local flavours at this weekemd only High Tea Buffet at Bar Intermezzo located within Orchard Hotel.

From the fragrant perfection of Signature Singapore Laksa and succulent tenderness of Kong Bak Pau to savoury sweetness of carrot cake and creamy decadence of Durian Pengat, you can enjoy delectable spread of local flavours right here.

We also enjoyed some diy moments at their diy station for Kueh Pie Tee and Rojak. We especially enjoyed their assorted dimsum, chicken curry with Roti Jala and Assorted Nonya Kueh.

text: Location is excellent. 1 to 2 mins walk to a 24 hours 7 eleven, Burger King and Mac Donalds and many restaurants. ADD ON Ôºö Extended my stay for another 2 nights, and realised that once after 12 midnight there is less noise from pub as live band stops. You can hear fade music at Room B ( the 16 female pods) but I solved it by listening to music on my earpiece and I usually sleep at 1 am hence it doesnt affect me as much. I think it will be quieter at Room A ( mixed pods) as it is further away. I paid around $38 per night and stayed at a corner lower deck pod. It is definitely value for money if you are looking at a clean capsule hotel at a good location. Honestly, throughout the 3 nights, I slept well, there wasn't any noise from the other pods as this place is relatively new hence it is not fully occupied thus not many people walking in and out.

text:
Type: Private Capsule Room

Unfortunately, despite having lived in countless of hostels & hotels daily for a 1 years+, my experience here has been abnormally claustrophobic and noisy. It was certainly not worth staying... (I paid about S$70+ per night for it)

The private room is no different from sleeping in a store room with no windows. The lack of a single light from outside is the same as living in a black hole. Air ventilation is close to none, I had a hard time breathing to which, sleeping in bunk bed would be better.

The worst thing? You can find the room trembling to the loud music from the nightclub above which I remember was way after 1am... Entry into the private room operates by downloading an

They only provide in house showers rooms which are small and lacks space & hook for your clothes + essentials. The building‚Äôs toilet outside of the hostel feels super hot located just beside the air duct vacuuming heat from kitchens below.

The large coworking table & local beverage is great. But overall, not worth returning.

Location is great for tourist who wish to visit the Asian Museums and drink alcohol along Boat Quay, Clark Quay etc, and visit the Merlion.

title: Bluewaters Pods 11 North Canal Road
text:
My recent stay here booked through Agoda was a series of unacceptable shortcomings. Upon arrival at midnight, the complete lack of signage for the establishment made finding it an exasperating experience.  Exhausted from travel, I finally located the place with the assistance of a helpful stranger ‚Äì on the top floor of a building where even other tenants seemed unaware of its existence.

The frustration continued at the check-in.  There was no staffed front desk, and the information provided by the staff regarding check-in details was incomplete and ultimately unusable. Two other guests faced similar issues, struggling with incorrect access codes. Thankfully, another guest  assisted us in deciphering the unclear instructions, a process that consumed a frustrating thirty minutes.  Despite repeated attempts to reach staff through the Agoda app, no assistance was provided.

The deficiencies continued within the capsule room itself. The extreme lack of ventilation and absence of at least a small fan inside the capsule made for an uncomfortably hot environment. Even with the curtain partially open for a semblance of air circulation, the temperature remained stifling.  As if the physical discomfort wasn't enough, the night was plagued by excessive noise. Loud karaoke music from a nearby bar echoed through the walls throughout the early hours, hindering sleep. Furthermore, the capsule design offered minimal soundproofing, allowing even minor noises from other guests to easily disrupt the tranquility of the room.

The final indignity came in the form of the shared bathroom. Located outside the hotel itself, it was a dirty and inconvenient communal facility.  This unsanitary situation was the final straw.  The next morning, I promptly checked out, deeply dissatisfied with the entire experience.  This stay fell far short of even the most basic hospitality standards. If you prioritize comfort and a well-maintained environment, I strongly recommend avoiding this accommodation entirely.

The service here is super nice and friendly. Have a good time staying, especially thanks to Fikri! He is so helpful and friendly during my stay. The other staff are nice as well.

Overall, I love this hostel. Have been coming back multiple times whenever I visit Singapore.

Just one minus point is the bar upstairs, yet they are working on this problems (in which I appreciate since they listen to customers ideas and opinions).

title: Bluewaters Pods 11 North Canal Road
text:
This hostel was unfortunately a letdown. The check-in process was a headache, with gaps in the instructions. Despite reaching out to customer service for help, I still ended up having to figure it out mostly on my own and it took way too long. Self-check-in isn't a new concept, but the way it's handled here is disjointed and leaves a lot to be desired.

Finding the place is next to impossible, and the instructions didn't give the actual location. Like others, I had to rely on reviews to track it down. (PS: If you're struggling to find the entrance, look for a lift inside an unmarked entrance at the back of an alley at a different address ‚Äî it's at number 13, not 11...)

Once inside, the cleanliness wasn't up to par and trash was scattered around. There's a loud club in the same building that shakes the floor all night. At that point, I decided to cut my losses and found another place to stay.

I appreciated that the staff responded to my concerns by email and we had a polite dialogue, but they refused to provide a refund for future nights I wasn't going to stay. It would have been nice to see more flexibility given the circumstances.

Overall, the experience here wasn't good, and they were content to keep my money despite providing a poor experience. I'd explore other options in the area next time.

Edit: in their public response to my review, the hostel claimed they would be reaching out to me directly to address a concern. I never heard from them.

text:
Love the vibes here. Atelier Lounge & Bar ‚Äì Where Sophistication Meets Soul in the Heart of Singapore

From plush seating to mood-lit interiors, every detail invites you to unwind ‚Äî whether you‚Äôre here for a laid-back afternoon tea or a spirited evening rendezvous.

The menu? Refined yet approachable. Think artisanal cocktails crafted with flair, premium wines, and curated spirits alongside thoughtful bites and sharing platters. Their mixologists don‚Äôt just serve drinks ‚Äî they tell stories through every glass, whether you‚Äôre sipping a bold negroni or a fragrant floral gin creation.

Whether you‚Äôre networking, decompressing, or simply indulging, Atelier Lounge & Bar delivers that sweet spot of calm and class. It‚Äôs not just a bar ‚Äî it‚Äôs a conversation starter, a retreat, a mood.

The big downside is that there is nothing special about the atmosphere and hotel guests transit through on way to pool, restaurant, and other places. So hard to enjoy drinks when a couple kids come shrieking through.
Overall, I would not recommend this bar.  Definitely only for those staying at the hotel and even then, not sure I would get drinks there.

title: Marine Mammal Habitat
text:
I think this place is worth 3 stars at the most. I'm only giving this grade because the dolphin trainers were well-organized and made sure that the participants were aware of the safety regulations.

We were willing to pay the price for the dolphin experience because we know it costs money to upkeep the place, give dolphins good food (I see they are always feeding them well) etc.

BUT the overall experience was not good. The toilets are not in the best condition. As an observer, I was bitten ferociously by mosquitoes while waiting for my family to finish their experience with the dolphins. And the worst thing is, they did not provide any towels when the participants got out of the water. It was cold and we still had to listen to the debrief... and wait, listen to their sales pitch for the photographs.

The photographs are such a rip-off, but guess what - we end up having to buy it because the staff are extremely strict about not bringing in your own cameras or phones. 2 photos that cost close to $170. It was the cheapest deal that we could find. The quality of the photos aren't even that great and the photo frame is flimsy. This left a a sour taste in my mouth and I feel so embarrassed about the kind of visitor experience that we are showing to international tourists who just want to come here for a good time with their family...

title: CS Fresh Great World
text:
I am a frequent customer at CS fresh Great World City. After my workouts at True Fitness, I usually come here for groceries and often buy a roasted chicken from the counter. The staff have always been helpful ‚Äî most of them willingly cut the chicken into 4 pieces for me upon request.

However, I have repeatedly encountered poor service from one staff member named Lily. On several occasions, she refused to cut the chicken, giving various reasons ‚Äî such as ‚Äúthe chicken is on sale‚Äù or ‚Äúit‚Äôs the weekend and there are too many customers.‚Äù This has happened multiple times, yet her colleagues have always been able to provide the same service without issue.

When I raised this with the store manager, Mr. Puah, he confirmed that cutting the chicken is part of their service, regardless of whether it is on sale or how busy it is. I hope top management will address this inconsistency so that customers can enjoy a consistent level of service from all staff members.

title: CS Fresh Great World
text:
It was my first time visiting this Cold Storage outlet to buy fresh fish. I selected a larger piece and asked the service staff to help cut it into smaller portions and pack them into separate bags, so I could cook them on different days.

However, after the staff finished cutting the fish, I noticed he did not wear gloves during the entire process. Even more concerning, he handled the raw fish with bare hands and didn‚Äôt wash his hands before placing the pieces into the plastic bags. Later, when he handled another clean bag for storing other raw meat, he still didn‚Äôt wash his hands beforehand.

This is a serious hygiene issue that could lead to cross-contamination and increase the risk of foodborne illness or even something more severe. It was extremely upsetting and unacceptable to witness such unsafe food handling practices.

I sincerely hope the management takes this matter seriously and ensures all staff are properly trained before assigning them to such important roles. No customer should have to worry about food poisoning due to poor hygiene standards.

The cooked food section and Japanese sushi offerings are impressively varied, and there‚Äôs also a large area dedicated to fresh flowers and greenery, adding a touch of freshness to the shopping experience.

The checkout area is spacious with plenty of counters, so waiting times are usually minimal.
Overall, it‚Äôs a great grocery spot that combines quality, variety, and an enjoyable shopping atmosphere.

title: CS Fresh Great World
text:
I was browsing the bread section and noticed there were no staff around, so I casually looked around the area to see if anyone might be able to assist. I spotted a lady at the meat section but wasn‚Äôt sure if she was also responsible for the bread, so I simply continued waiting, I wasn‚Äôt upset or in a hurry, just calmly looking for someone to help.

Unexpectedly, the lady from the meat section walked over and said to me in a rude tone, ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt know how to open your mouth and ask? No one knows you need anything if you don‚Äôt ask.‚Äù I was taken aback by her attitude, but I calmly pointed to the bread I wanted and asked her to help cut it.

After she finished, she repeated the same rude comment again about how if I didn‚Äôt open my mouth, no one would know, again, in a condescending tone.

I want to emphasize that I really wasn‚Äôt angry or trying to find fault at all about not being attended to. But the way she spoke to me, completely unprovoked, was unnecessary and frankly, quite upsetting. Her tone and choice of words turned what was a perfectly normal situation into an unpleasant one.

I hope this can be looked into, as basic courtesy and professionalism really make a difference in customer experience.

Thank you.

text:
I‚Äôd like to raise a concern about a very rude staff member at your store, his behavior has been consistently unprofessional, and I strongly urge CS Fresh to review this issue.

A few weeks ago, someone had spilled a drink on the floor. As I was pushing a trolley and unknowingly approached the area, this staff member stood nearby and abruptly shouted ‚ÄúOi!‚Äù before pointing at the spill. His expression was extremely hostile!
almost as if to say, ‚ÄúAre you blind?‚Äù It was unnecessarily aggressive and humiliating.

On another occasion, I witnessed him act rudely toward a couple browsing at the bakery section. He arrived with multiple carts and attempted to push through a narrow space without saying ‚ÄúExcuse me‚Äù or asking politely. Instead, he glared at the couple with an exaggerated, wide-eyed stare, silently pressuring them to move. Startled, they quickly stepped aside. It was uncomfortable to witness.

Later, when I went to pay for my items, I told the cashier that I‚Äôd return shortly to grab a few more packs of blueberries. I placed my cart aside temporarily. This same staff member then ordered me to push my cart over and return to the bakery area, even though I had already informed the cashier of my plan. It felt controlling and unnecessary.

Fortunately, another staff member noticed and kindly offered to help move my cart. His helpful attitude stood in stark contrast to the rude behavior I‚Äôve described.

Staff training and professionalism are essential to the shopping experience. Customers should never feel intimidated or disrespected. I sincerely hope CS Fresh takes this feedback seriously and addresses this individual‚Äôs behavior appropriately.

title: THE CHEVRONS Aviary KTV
text:
1-Star Review (Would give zero if possible)
The worst karaoke experience ever

It‚Äôs a Friday night and we arrived at this karaoke place around 9 PM and were given a room that had apparently already started at 9, which we didn‚Äôt mind. Not realizing it was a bar setting, we made the mistake of bringing our own drinks. Shortly after starting our session, the 1st female staff member entered to inform us that outside drinks weren‚Äôt allowed. We apologized, explained it was our first time there, and we would order food and drinks from the venue. She was understanding and told us not to do it again.

However, things quickly turned ridiculous. Within the next 5 minutes, a 2nd female staff member came in to repeat the same message. We again apologized and reiterated that we had placed orders with them.

Then, less than 2 minutes later, a 3rd male staff member entered to tell us again that outside drinks weren‚Äôt allowed and warned he‚Äôd come back to check. We complied and placed the drinks into a paper bag. But before even a minute had passed, a fourth staff member entered, this time asking to confiscate our drinks and store them at the counter. We refused, as the drinks were already opened and half-consumed ‚Äî we had no idea what might happen to them once out of our sight.

Throughout the entire 2-hour session, staff continued to peek into our room repeatedly, making us feel like we were under surveillance. It felt less like a karaoke session and more like being in a monitored holding cell. Aren‚Äôt they busy on a Friday night, why would they do it to such extent?

If outside drinks are strictly prohibited, the staff could have simply refused us entry or asked us to leave at the start. Instead, they allowed us in, took our card, and then spent the rest of the time interrupting and policing us, ruining what should have been an enjoyable night.

Absolutely terrible service. I would give zero stars if I could. Avoid this place at all costs

title: Best Denki
text: Bought a Panasonic fridge from BD IMM in May for my elderly mother. It was delivered a few days later but it broke down the following day. Only my mum was at home to receive the fridge on that day. The technician came the next day and reported the issue was due to ‚Äúsystem failure‚Äù. Reported the matter to BD and requested for a 1 to 1 exchange which they did a few days later. Upon closer investigation, it was discovered that the fridge was delivered without any box packaging (red flag) and also the Instruction Manual was not wrapped in the usual sealed plastic bag (another red flag). Filed a complaint to Panasonic (no reply yet after 10 days) and BD (only received a call from a warehouse person claiming that the defective fridge was new). For me, it‚Äôs either a Grade B stock or a repaired set or a display set. No official explanation from BD and Panasonic. Very disappointed with the whole episode. title: Little Big Coffee Roasters
text:
I stumbled upon Little Big C R not too long ago, and I‚Äôm so glad I did! Tucked away in a cozy corner of biopolis, this place is a perfect blend of charm, comfort, and quality.

The coffee? Absolutely outstanding. I have had their signature inhouse blends. Easily one of the best cups I‚Äôve had in Singapore.

What truly sets this caf√© apart is the warm, friendly service. The baristas were incredibly knowledgeable and happy to recommend beverages based on our preferences. You can tell they‚Äôre passionate about their craft.

The ambience is another win: authentic raw nofrills cafe, and plenty of natural light make it a great spot to chill, catch up on work, or meet friends.

We also shared a slice of their homemade banana, lemon cake, which was divine‚Äîmoist, fragrant, and not too sweet. I‚Äôll definitely be coming back to try their other small bakes items.

If you‚Äôre a coffee enthusiast or just looking for a peaceful spot to unwind, Little Big C R is a must-visit. Highly recommended!

title: Accord Auto Services Pte Ltd
text:
MY THOUGHTS ON ACCORD AUTO SERVICES @ 09 JUN 2025

I visited Accord Auto Services (Accord) at its 1009 Bukit Merah Lane workshop Monday, 02 June 2025 before my travel on Sat, 07 June 2025 and I like to share my good impressions on the competence and professionalism of the team especially, Gilbert and Ah Hao.

I observed that Accord has the precise BMW diagnostic tools and professional expertise to diagnose and systematically assess ‚Äúthe morning cold start idling‚Äù issue which I have been experiencing for a few months.

From checks and research thus far, I understand that the cold start issue (apparently common to many older BMW cars) could be caused by (1) some faulty ECU sensors; or/and (2) clogged fuel injector/sin cylinders; and/or (3) overnight fuel injectors‚Äô bleeding‚Ä¶

I must say that I truly appreciate the Accord service team‚Äôs professional diligence and comprehensive cum thorough diagnosis of the car‚Äôs engine and ECU sensors. The diagnostic process took about two odd hours and the Accord team managed to diagnose that the Nitrogen Oxide or NOx sensor [which was replaced in July 2023 by another workshop but unsure if that NOx sensor replaced then had been correctly coded] is faulty and unwittingly send erroneous signals to the ECU and causing the morning cold start and (unfortunate cum annoying) rough idling issue ‚Ä¶

On the very next day, Tue, 03 Jun 2025, the Accord  team promptly texted the quote and estimated downtime to replace the NOx sensor. As I am travelling now, I look forward to arranging the NOx sensor replacement with Accord when I return from my travel  in late June  2025.

I shall also try to update/ cross-share and cross-learn further for those who have same or other engine issues concerning their BMW cars.

text:
I had my bumper fixed here in 2020, found the place on Google, happy with the prompt quotations given via WhatsApp based on my photos. When I sent my car in, I was attended to by Jing Rong who is down-to-earth, no drama, explaining the repair process clearly. The price quoted is much cheaper than 2 other places that I asked, where they acted like my damage was irreparable and needed replacement parts. Jing Rong simply stated what he could and could not do, and how much it costed, which was a very reasonable price. The car came back good as new and I knew this was the place I would go to if I ever needed another repair.

Now in 2025, two of my car doors got damaged. Jing Rong attended to me again, was transparent and prompt in giving me the quotation. No up-sell, and updated me with realistic turnaround time. Bonus, he was attentive and reminded me to take my valuables with me, but I still forgot some things, so I texted him to help me with safekeeping and he was ever so patient and helpful. text:
I have always buy my groceries at Giant Ghim Moh. For the last couple years, I have been bringing my own grocery bags due to environment reason. Giant staffs are friendly and helpful, except for 1 person, ms. Huang or Shuang, one with short boyish hairstyle (I didn't get her surname). She has never assisted to pack my groceries whenever I bring my own shopping bags. She would only pack when I pass her my bags and ask for her help while I make payment or putting my cash into my wallet.

Never ever have I wanted to complain about her but base on my last experience is my last drawn with her. I asked her to help me to pack my groceries while I put my money back into my purse (I have pack half of it myself) and yet, she went ahead and process transaction for other customer. In the end, I pack by myself.

Other staffs usually help me pack my groceries into my bags without me asking for their help. That includes cashier staffs at FairPrice or Cold Storage.

I think, it is part of their respnsibilities to pack for their customer whethet they pay for plastic bag or using their own shopping bag. Unless Giants has a different policy.

If customer has to packed their own groceries when they bring their own shopping bag, might as well add in more self check out counters and please make sure self check out counters are working. The machines are not even working most of the days.

I hope Giant would take my feedback into consideration and improve customer shopping experience from good to excellent.

title: The Room @ Bugis
text: Stayed for 4 nights in July 2025. The location is good, just a few minutes walk from Bugis MRT station, and there are many restaurants nearby.However, I give it one star out of five. I don't know about the women's room, but there is only one water tap (sink) for the men's room for over 50 people. There are only four toilets and showers, two separate ones and two in each room. This doesn't seem to violate Singapore law, but it clearly shows the owner's attitude towards his guests. In the morning, you often have to fight with other people over the sink, and it's normal to wait 5-10 minutes. It's not cleaned and dirty.There are also numerous shoes and slippers left in a mess at the entrance, including disposable slippers that have been thrown away. Footwear is not permitted inside the building, but the floors are dirty and indoor beach sandals are a must.There is a refrigerator, but it is not organized at all, and there is rotten food left there, giving off a foul odor, so new guests should assume that it is practically unusable. The price is close to the lowest in the area, so the clientele is extremely poor. The room is small, and there are many suitcases at the entrance, so the door sometimes cannot be opened. There is no space to pack luggage inside the room.

title: Alchemist The Mill
text:
You have to come here on a weekday afternoon. That‚Äôs when you can enjoy this gem in all its full glory.

During peak hours, it‚Äôs just bad. People talking as if they own the place, hogging the seats and just being impolite to the staff there. No please and no thank yous‚Ä¶ but the staff always remains friendly. I‚Äôm probably the courtesy Nazi. ü•π

I always get my drinks extra hot and extra hot they come. The bites are easy on the tummy but on a quiet day, the drinks, the bites and the feel of being there watching the staff at work becomes somewhat magical - work of the alchemist.

A hidden gem far from other places that are packed with consistently good coffee.

title: Soul Spa
text:
Called and arranged a 90-min session with Jesy. Spoke to her about my body aching areas and she was very well attentive to them. She knows how to provide deep press massages, and helped to relief off a lot of air pockets from my daily workout stints on my arms, ribs, thighs etc.  Her number of  experience years in this field tells it all.

To know my physical challenges, I always have to walk a lot daily during my outdoor work covering some distances of 3km to 5km and i additionally perform my weekly weekend runs abt 5km to 10kms.

I looked out for the reliefs and recovery after all the pain pressed from the massages and she did very well from applying any kind of overstressing pressure on my muscles and joints.

Plus i felt so much better in terms of gaining more energy and ease of more physical mobility after having a few hours rest at home after the session.

Im now more than ever looking forward to having more sessions with her in the future.

Thank you Soul Spa for having one of the most experienced staff like Jesy! üëçüëçüëçüëçüëç

title: Phuture
text:
It's a scam... The ushers at the entrance are very arrogant, talk to you as if they want to beat you up!

I bought a voucher on Grab and the terms and condition only stated that the voucher should be redeemed on either Wednesday, Friday or Saturday. I went on a Saturday night, and showed them that I was there to redeem my voucher. The staff at the entrance told me I couldn‚Äôt use it because they had a special guest that night and wanted to 'avoid losses.'

When I asked which terms and conditions could prevent me from entering because of the presence of special guests, they told me it's their decision now and they would inform Grab partnership team next time. It becomes my own problem and I should deal with Grab myself instead!

Interestingly, the staff then admitted that the voucher is a clickbait as they don't want the customer to redeem the voucher, even though the voucher has stated that it should be redeemed within the specified day and period.

Does this imply that Zouk being a big and trusted corporation are playing click bait to cheat the customers? This is not only unprofessional but also completely disregards the rights of your customers!

When I asked to record their statement to raise dispute against Grab, one of the staff touched my phone and raised her tone towards me. This is completely unacceptable. First, did you have permission to touch my personal property? Second, how can you not take responsibility for what you've said, yet still represent Zouk?

I asked for their manager's email and emailed them the day after. But even after 4 days, there's no reply at all. So GO AT YOUR OWN RISK!

title: FairPrice Finest Zhong Shan Park
text:
Honestly, a downsized FairPrice Finest Zhong Shan after renovation is unexpected. While it spots a stylish layout, more upscale interior and environment with new lightings and furnishings, the original premise on L2 shrinks quite significantly; Mr D.I.Y., HCL Education Centre and Royce Dental Surgery take up the remaining floor space.

Given a smaller supermarket space after revamp, product assortment isn't as wide as before (some sections and products have been removed). Kinda' miss the pre-renovated FairPrice...

title: FairPrice Finest Zhong Shan Park
text:

I do agree with many that the downsize is a bit disappointing but I can understand this Fairprice is not as popular as others so they gave up some space. I can‚Äôt find everything I want here, but if you‚Äôre not picky it‚Äôs honestly as good as any. Check it out while it‚Äôs still spick and span :)

title: FairPrice Finest Zhong Shan Park
text:
I visited the revamped store recently. It's looking very nice and fancy. Unfortunately, the store has been reduced in size. While the old Fairprice took up the entire floor, the new store only uses about half (there's a small Mr. DIY and a dentist or something utilizing the other half of the floor space).

I did find everything I needed while shopping, but I missed the "international aisles" the store used to have. Now, for example, Japanese food stuff has been reduced to a few small  shelves.

The store has always struggled with aircon problems but for some weird reason, it's gotten worse since the reno. Was warm and stuffy. Hope they get that sorted out soon.

title: FairPrice Finest Zhong Shan Park

Even coming from Australia, I found Singapore to be cheaper, especially for groceries. I loved the assortments of little juices available too. I ensured to stock up on some of my favourite snacks to bring back home.

text: Long wait with only a few patients. Unusual long interval between one patient finishing and calling the next one. Doctor was not professional and not caring, just give medicine and ask to go specialist if further symptoms. No diagnose given at all. Not even asking if MC is needed. Not recommended.

title: The Clinic Group @ Fusionopolis
text:
Visited twice for check up and vaccination. Doctors are efficient. I conveyed my feedback to the anchor Dr Aamir. He promised to speak to the receptionists so hope situation will improve in the future.
Receptionists have poor understanding of workflow, gave wrong information and still talked down on patients and arrogant.
1. Enquired on COVID vaccine and RSV vaccine. COVID vaccine needs to register on MOH webpage but NOT the clinic webpage (as advised to scan QR code of clinic at the counter). Only acknowledged this mistake after I offered twice to show them my phone.Told me no RSV vaccine available when it‚Äôs shown on website with price. Clearly they don‚Äôt even know what vaccine services are provided at the clinic and are too lazy to even look up upon request.
2. Vaccine record was missed by the first doctor to upload to healthHUB. Could be easily corrected by checking with the doctor. However receptionists first dismissed my request and told me to check with MOH??! Only upon insisting did they register me to clarify with the doctor who admitted it was a missed upload and amended on the spot.
3. Maid health check up records. We told the receptionists that we need a copy and the receptionists said they‚Äôd call us back in about 1 week to collect result. No phone call or follow up. Had to walk in to get result again. Told today that the routine practice is to just upload result to MOM as most customers don‚Äôt want a copy?
All mistakes could have been cordially resolved but the receptionists talking down on patients simply made the experience truly unpleasant.

text:
The doctor was not professionally dressed and his prescriptions were also a bit incorrect but he dismissed my inputs at the same time. When I asked him about care measures he did not mention, but I read on Harvard and WebMD (without citing the websites) he told me not to follow advice on the internet, that I could be reading incorrect information. And those care measures were on the instruction of the medication he gave me. He also told me to go back to see him if the medicine doesn't work after some time. I know from my reading that it will take at least 6 months to see results, but he said to go back to him in a few weeks if I don't see results. This advice again does not match up correctly with the medicine instruction which said 6-12 months.

I got the correct medicine, but poor instructions from him on how to use it. I felt that he doesn't really know how to take care of my medical issue, gave incorrect advice, and in general was not taking his job and myself very seriously.

text: Shopper at City Square Mall NTUC beware of the counter China lady cutting raw meat. I bought one whole Salmon fish for $50 and asked the lady to cut them into individual slices and packed them individually. I also asked her how long I can store them in the freezer and she said not longer than 2 months. I saw her packed them individually in bags of 2 slices so I didn‚Äôt check the bag after I reached home and immediately stored in the freezer. Three days later, I removed them from the freezer and realised that she had bags with 2 slices and there is one big bag with a harden chunk of 4 thick slices of salmon which was so hardened that I had to let it thaw under running water. This is unbelievable as I know that fish after thawing is not advisable to store back in the freezer. The salmon slices become all smashed up after thawing (see photos). Feel so annoyed and disappointed with this type of service.

text:
Rating: 1/5 Stars ‚≠êÔ∏è

Saw LiteMobile on TikTok FYP for a burn mark on my LCD screen. Went to their branch, got the repair with a "3-month warranty." I pointed out a scratch immediately, but they said it was just dirt! Now there's a bright white spot that wasn't there before! The manufacturer is just rabak!

Their customer service (via WhatsApp) is APPALLING. Instant replies from another's phone pretending to be a new customer, but "bohlayan" when I tried to claim my warranty. After ranting to "Desmond" on WhatsApp, he offered a refund AND a new LCD. I refused because their rabak customer service made me lose all trust. They suddenly claimed my phone had a bloated battery and could damage the screen, wanting to "check" it. Sketchy!

LiteMobile needs to prioritize warranty claims and acknowledge issues instead of dismissing them. First and last time customer here. Save yourself the trouble and go somewhere else!

#Singapore #CustomerServiceFail #TikTokMadeMeTryItAndItFailed #WarrantyNightmare #Rabak #ShadyBusiness

title: Squad Workshop
text:
I had an excellent experience with Squad Workshop. I brought in a car I was considering buying for a pre-purchase inspection, and they did a very thorough check‚Äîidentifying a major problem that I would have completely missed. This saved me from making an expensive mistake.

They were responsive during office hours, professional in their communication, and clear in explaining their findings. The inspection was detailed, well-documented, and gave me full confidence in their assessment. Highly recommended for anyone who wants an honest and meticulous PPI in Singapore.

title: Squad Workshop
text: Was introduced to Squad Workshop through a friend‚Äôs recommendation and have since visited twice ‚Äî once for engine oil servicing and another for rotor and brake pad replacement. Both experiences were very good, and I‚Äôm very satisfied with their services. Royston and Meryl were friendly, helpful, and genuinely passionate about their business which is rare these days. My go-to workshop from now on üî•

title: Squad Workshop
text:
Fair, honest and competent - this is the best workshop I have ever gone to. The team are always updated on the latest technological developments in cars and have in-depth knowledge on automotive products. Prices are fair, transparent and you can always be assured your car is in the best hands.

Need a service, decarbonization of the engine or aftermarket upgrades to improve the ride? Squad is the place to be. I had issues with my boot mechanism and the team solved it in minutes. That's competency for you.

I have been servicing my car here ever since it opened and have recommended dozens of friends. their service and knowledge is 5* all the way. Please ignore any 1* reviews trying to bring down the reputation of SQUAD.

title: Squad Workshop
text: Always the trusted workshop to bring my car in! From handling my accident to giving great advice on how to maintain my car ‚ù§Ô∏è Meryl and Royston are a great team together! Show them the love and support

title: Squad Workshop
text:
‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê Outstanding Service for My VW Passat B8 2.0! Huge Thanks to Boss Royston & Lady Boss Meryl!

As a meticulous owner of a Volkswagen Passat B8 2.0, finding a workshop I can implicitly trust is paramount. **Squad Workshop in Singapore has not only met but exceeded every expectation!** This review is a heartfelt thank you to the incredible team, especially **Boss Royston and Lady Boss Meryl**, for their exceptional service.

**Why Squad Workshop stands out for your Passat (or any VW!):**

1.  **Precision & Expertise (Royston is a Legend!):** Boss Royston truly knows Volkswagens inside and out. His diagnostic skills are top-notch. He doesn't just fix symptoms; he finds the *root cause* efficiently and explains it clearly. Working on my Passat B8 2.0, his attention to detail and understanding of its specific engineering were evident. I felt completely confident my car was in expert hands.
2.  **Transparency & Trust:** No guesswork, no unnecessary upsell. Royston and the team clearly explain what needs doing, why, and the options available. You get honest assessments and fair quotes. As an owner who cares deeply about the car, this transparency is invaluable.
3.  **Exceptional Customer Care (Meryl is Amazing!):** Lady Boss Meryl is the heart of the operation! Her communication is fantastic ‚Äì prompt, clear, and friendly. From scheduling appointments to updates during the service, she ensures everything runs smoothly and you're always informed. She genuinely cares about customers and creates a welcoming, professional environment.
4.  **Meticulous Workmanship:** The work performed on my Passat was flawless. Everything felt precise, clean, and done to a very high standard. They treat your car with the respect it deserves.
5.  **Passionate Ownership:** It's rare to find a workshop where *both* owners are so visibly passionate and hands-on. Royston's technical mastery combined with Meryl's customer focus makes them an unbeatable team. You can feel their dedication to quality and customer satisfaction in everything they do.
6.  **Fair Pricing:** You absolutely get what you pay for ‚Äì high-quality, reliable work from true specialists. The value for the level of expertise and care is excellent.

**To Boss Royston and Lady Boss Meryl:** Thank you both sincerely! Your dedication, expertise, and genuine care have made maintaining my Passat B8 2.0 a stress-free and positive experience. You've earned a customer for life. Thanks for looking after my car like it was your own!

**To fellow VW (or any car) owners in Singapore:** If you want a workshop that combines **deep technical expertise (especially for VW Group cars!), transparent communication, meticulous work, and genuinely caring ownership**, look no further than Squad Workshop. Stop searching ‚Äì you've found the best! **Highly, HIGHLY recommended!**

**Thanks again, Boss Royston and Lady Boss Meryl! You guys are simply the best!**
**- One Very Satisfied & Meticulous Passat B8 Owner**

title: Luss Restaurant & Bar
text:
We went there yesterday evening for a Valentine's Day dinner, and though it was a last minute reservation, the restaurant staff made sure me and my wife were seated comfortably. They even gifted my wife with roses.

The interior of the restaurant & bar are well-designed & quite newly renovated. Located amongst the lush greenery of nostalgic Portsdown area, we walked through rows of magical flower arches to the restaurant. The atmosphere inside & outside the restaurant was lovely, with alfresco sitting as well; the staff are incredibly friendly and attentive, and the cocktails & food are delicious. Truly a little gem tucked away in the outskirts. Highly recommend!

title: Luss Restaurant & Bar
text:
My partner and I came here for Valentine's yesterday! We came down right after school, and even though I was carrying a bulky bag with my wrestling shoes dangling on the side, they welcomed us without complaint. From the steps up to the last meal, the food, service and atmosphere were excellent.

We were told that there was a bustling crowd right before we came, so 9pm seems to be the quietest time, in case anyone has the same idea for a date!

The food: We ordered the Pasta, Mala, Pork Belly Skewers, Crab Meat and Buns, two Mocktails, and the Cheese Platter. Each one was as good as the next, and the prices were very reasonably priced for the amazing quality.

The place: The restaurant is situated around a quiet, off the road curb, with stairs leading up to it. It is nested within beautiful nature, with air-conditioned indoor seating, and outdoor seating as well. The restaurant's manager, I believe, was extremely accommodating, and we spoke for a bit. She also adjusted the air-condition for us when we felt chilly.

Before we left, she gave us two roses, which are very appreciated =)

Overall, the whole experience was just really, really pleasant. This will be our new date night spot, and honestly we wanted to gatekeep this...but we also want this place to thrive, so there you go! Visit this place, you will not regret it.

Side note: As two young University students, we aren't normally paid much attention to at restaurants, which is all well and good since I'm happy having our alone time, but it is a really appreciated and welcoming gesture from the waiters and manager to speak to us. A refreshing experience indeed!

title: Queenstown Polyclinic
text:
I had a really disappointing experience at the polyclinic today. I came in as a walk-in at 730am today right before the opening time at 8am because I was vomiting badly and feeling extremely lightheaded in the morning. I‚Äôve also been visiting this clinic for an eye infection, so it made sense to come back here.

At the registration counter, I told the Chinese lady that I was feeling very unwell and couldn‚Äôt go to a GP because I was lightheaded and could throw up anytime. I also explained that I‚Äôm on ComCare and can‚Äôt afford to go to a private clinic. Still, she said they will only see case that is urgent and that the doctor‚Äôs schedule was fully booked, and just told me to buy medicine from the pharmacy.

But I‚Äôd already taken medicine, and I needed a doctor to assess what was actually wrong. I felt helpless.

I‚Äôm really grateful to the Indian lady near the self-check-in kiosk who saw how pale I looked and told me to keep checking the app for any available slots. She was the only one who showed concern when I could barely see clearly anymore.

It‚Äôs frustrating and disheartening to be turned away when you‚Äôre visibly unwell. The least u could do is make an effort and go an extra mile.I hope they can better assess such situations, especially for those of us facing financial difficulties.

title: Queenstown Polyclinic
text: Zero if I could. It is stated clearly on the website that we can walk in for our flu vaccination. I arrived at 2:50pm to walk in with my sister who had an appointment for flu vaccination. The counter staff was rude and insist that I cannot walk in for flu vaccination even when I told her the website clearly stated that we could. She denied and cut me off rudely with a ‚ÄúJune 4th is your earliest appointment date‚Äù. Keep insisting the system say cannot. However, my sister ask the nurse and she say that usually walk in appointments are allowed. My family members usually walk in for flu vaccinations and there‚Äôs no issue. There‚Äôs clearly an inconsistency between your staff and what is stated on the website. This speaks volume and shows the need for you to retrain your staff.

I rarely write reviews but this workshop deserves it. Scammy, unprofessional and dishonest, so let me share my experience.

My car had issues with my side mirror, so i sent it down to be fixed as per my dealership (Vincar) instructions.

First off, they never informed me that the car had to be collected the next day, was under the impression it could be collected in the same day. I stayed in the area and only when it was 5pm and I gave them a call, then they told me it could be collected the next day.

Secondly, collected the car, mirror was jerky. They assured me it was a new part issue, tried to put some oil but issue was not resolved.

Lastly and the worse part, I just discovered these incapable staff curbed my rim when my car was with them and painted it over black which was why I didn't realise when I collected the car. Only realised when I was washing my own car and realised they didn't sand the part down. I was never informed of this and trying to cover this up just shows how dishonest they are.

Honestly, a bunch of unprofessional and dishonest people working here. Please avoid them at all cost.

title: Royal Albatross - Luxury Tall Ship
text:
Just to feedback that we attended the dinner cruise on 24/8 Night and had a very wonderful experience on the Royal Albatross, and it was our first time attending.

However, there is 1 issue we need to highlight.

We sat next to the bar counter, on the first table when guests first enter and walk up the steps.
Everything was perfect except when eating the cake halfway, my wife bit on a staple bullet which she managed to extract from her mouth.

Thankfully, there was no injury or bleeding and we highlighted it to the waiter (Malay gentleman) who was very apologetic, immediately removed the cake and offered us a mocktail each FOC.
We had a lovely evening and do not want one negative issue to mar the whole experience.
Hence its unfortunate that this happened and hope you can investigate or highlight this with your birthday cake vendor to ensure that it doesnt happen again (I'm sure they can figure out where the staple bullet originated from).

Unfortunately, we were too shocked and forgot to take a photo, but just writing a note here for the record.
Post-dinner, i wrote an email to followup and close off this matter but did not receive a reply.
Hope it has been investigated and resolved. Ideally, i would have liked a refund on the cake alone too. It doesnt seem right to have paid for a cake with a staple bullet and which was thrown away half eaten.

title: Samsung Electronics
text:
The Most Pathetic Experience with Samsung ‚Äì Globally and in Singapore

If there were an award for disappointment, Samsung would win hands down. I trusted a globally renowned brand, paid a premium, and ended up with dead pixels on my screen. A quality control issue that has been reported by countless customers worldwide ‚Äî and yet, Samsung still pretends it‚Äôs not a problem.

But wait, it gets worse.

When I reached out to Samsung Singapore‚Äôs customer care, hoping for a solution, I was met with a level of indifference that was honestly insulting. Instead of helping, they had the audacity to say:
‚ÄúWe don‚Äôt know how you handled the phone.‚Äù
Seriously? That‚Äôs your response? Not only are your devices flawed, but now it‚Äôs the customer‚Äôs fault for expecting them to work?

I‚Äôm baffled. A flagship product with a screen issue and a support team that gaslights the user. This isn‚Äôt just bad service ‚Äî it‚Äôs pathetic. For a company that spends millions on marketing and brand image, your actual product quality and support are a disgrace.

To anyone considering a Samsung device: don‚Äôt.
Dead pixels, dead accountability, and dead silence when it comes to real customer issues.

text:
I am writing to express my frustration regarding an issue with a recent online purchase from your website. On January 11, 2025, I ordered the S24FE as part of a flash deal that included a power adapter and phone cover, opting for self-collection at the Samsung Experience Store at Compass One on January 14, 2025.

When I collected the phone on January 16, 2025, the power adapter and phone cover were missing. The staff explained that this was due to a website issue, which they had already reported to the Samsung hotline, and advised me to contact Samsung directly.

When I reached out to customer care, the manager's response was unprofessional, stating that disciplinary action would be taken against the retail staff for providing "incorrect" information. This is unacceptable, as the staff acknowledged the issue and responsibly reported it to headquarters.

If the flash deal did not include free items, why were they displayed in the cart during checkout? Customers should not have to endure misleading website information and inadequate issue resolution.

title: Samsung Electronics
text:
I purchased a brand-new Samsung S24 Ultra, expecting a premium product and service to match. Instead, I‚Äôve been met with nothing but frustration and disappointment.

Straight out of the box, the phone's camera was completely non-functional‚Äîa glaring hardware defect. For a device that is supposed to represent the pinnacle of Samsung‚Äôs innovation, this was an appalling start.

When I contacted Samsung, I made what I believe was a simple and reasonable request: an immediate replacement for a brand-new, defective product. To my shock, Samsung refused and insisted I take the phone to their service center for evaluation and potential repair. This demand is utterly unacceptable. Why should I, as a paying customer, have to jump through hoops to repair a product that was faulty from the start?

I escalated the issue, hoping for a better resolution. Two days later, Samsung called back‚Äîonly to repeat the same unhelpful response: no replacement, only repair. Their refusal to offer a replacement demonstrates a complete disregard for customer satisfaction. A company of Samsung‚Äôs stature should have a no-questions-asked replacement policy for defective products.

As if that wasn‚Äôt bad enough, the first customer service agent handling my case refused to provide his/her name when asked, showing a total lack of transparency and accountability. This evasive and dismissive behavior further underscores the inadequacies in Samsung‚Äôs customer service.

This entire ordeal‚Äîfrom receiving a defective product to the appallingly poor customer service‚Äîhas left me deeply disappointed. For anyone considering buying from Samsung, be warned: if something goes wrong, you‚Äôll be left to deal with a frustrating and unsympathetic system. This experience has seriously made me reconsider my loyalty to the brand.

Verdict: Avoid. Samsung's handling of this situation has been nothing short of a disaster.

text:
I would give ZERO stars if I could. Went there on Friday evening, ordered 2 Stout, 1 Heineken and 1 Truffle Fries- and th ordeal started

1. Waiter was forever busy chatting with other customers, took his own sweet time to take our order
2. Stout came after a few minutes but the Heineken didn't. Literally and I repeat without exaggerating, it must have taken at least 10-15 mins for the 3rd Beer that's on tap to come. I mean really?? How long does it take to pour a glass from a tap. It was clear that the service was really disappointing and it almost felt like some other customers were being given priority.
3. The fries never came btw. 30-45 mins of sitting there, no one said anything, Enquired and was told 'oh there's only one chef today. Could have given a heads-up before taking the order or at least told us while we were waiting forever just to have fries along with Beer.

Clearly they were incapable of handling Friday evening crowd. Never ever.

Went to Bar Bar Black sheep at HV after that and the service was impeccable. Food came within 5 mins of ordering, just fyi, so please just go there and save your Friday evening!!

üåøPancur Larangan is a water themed Garden set in a traditional Javanese style landscape with an intricately crafted beautiful wall mural feature depicting life in the Fort Canning Park from 1300s to 1800s.
ü¶ãVisitors are immediately drawn to the soft flowing water and it's beautiful surrounding landscape.
The entire place feels soothing and has a calming effect.
üçàIt let you slow down, soaking in the embience and enjoy the moment of peace and tranquility.
Fun fact:
ü´öPancur Larangan or "Forbidden Spring" was a bath place for the noble ladies of the royal court of Singapura during ancient time.
A spring used to flow from the west side of the hill.

Called around 11pm to check availability and was told by the counter staff, Jojo, that there was a slot in 15 minutes. I took a cab over, but just few minutes before arriving, she informed me that she had overlooked earlier bookings and that I would now have to wait an hour.

It was close to midnight, and with nowhere else to go, I asked if the cab fare could be reimbursed given the sudden change. Instead, I was met with excuses ‚Äî that she was new, crossed in and out of JB, had to pay rent, etc. She even went on to say Singaporeans are ‚Äúcalculative,‚Äù I told her it's not a matter of being a Singaporean but about professionalism, she insisted that she's right and that she never faced this when working in JB.

She later said that her boss wants to offer discount the next time I visit but with this kind of attitude and still expect me to return there again? No thank you.

title: Palace Therapy Spa Massage
text:
Walk-in as the shop structure was interesting. Old 3-storey building at end of Club Street.

Receptionist was unfortunately not welcoming or helpful. Was told to just go to room on 3rd floor with no guidance and low lighting. At room, you just need to change and get ready whilst waiting for masseur. When leaving, go down yourself and receptionist did not even acknowledge. (Deduct 1-star because of that)

On the other hand, masseur (didn‚Äôt ask her name) was really good. Ask about room temperature and her pressure throughout the session. Focused on the areas I was tight with. Several times during the session nearly dozed off even though the massage pressure was firm. At the end, even offered a hot drink.

Overall ambience was good. Old wooden buildings have more charm but wooden furniture will creak with food steps on the wooden floor as well as opening/closing doors. Maybe I was the only one but it was quiet and calm I.e. relaxing.

Room did not have a shower but at the floor level there was a shower room and toilet.

title: Palace Therapy Spa Massage
text:
One of, if not the WORST massages I've had. Spent $66 for an hour of back massage and I specifically asked for more pressure, but the masseuse immediately refused, saying, "Let's not, I don't want to injure you." Instead of an actual massage, I was left with what felt like a light caress over my entire body‚Äîcompletely ineffective and not at all what I paid for.

To make things worse, she even asked me which areas hurt the most, and I clearly mentioned my neck and back. Yet, she completely ignored my request and barely focused on those areas at all. What was the point of asking if she wasn‚Äôt going to listen?

The most disturbing part was that her touch felt unprofessional and extremely uncomfortable‚Äîalmost like I was being molested rather than receiving a massage. I‚Äôve never felt so uneasy during a session before, and I just wanted it to end as soon as possible.

Extremely disappointing, uncomfortable, and unprofessional. Would not recommend.

title: Great Shelford Tree
text:
Nestled in the cozy cul-de-sac on Shelford Road, the Great Shelford Tree is more than just a solitary tree; it‚Äôs an enchanting landmark and a celebrated tourist attraction that holds the power to transform your perspective and inspire profound reflection. This hidden gem, while seemingly simple, is a breathtaking reminder of nature‚Äôs beauty and resilience, standing tall against the backdrop of suburban life.

As you approach, the ambiance shifts. The gentle rustling of leaves and the occasional chirp of birds create a serene soundtrack that invites you to pause and breathe deeply. The tree, with its sprawling branches and lush green canopy, forms a natural cathedral, beckoning visitors to experience its tranquility. I vividly remember my first visit on a sunny afternoon; the light filtered through the leaves, casting intricate patterns on the ground, making it feel almost magical.

What truly sets the Great Shelford Tree apart is its history. Local lore suggests that this tree has stood for over a century, witnessing the ebb and flow of life around it. Generations of families have gathered beneath its branches for picnics, storytelling, and even proposals. I spoke to a local elder who fondly recounted how, as a child, he would climb its sturdy limbs, feeling like a king surveying his kingdom. It‚Äôs clear this tree has served as a silent witness to countless life events, each one adding to its mystique.

Visitors often come not just for the beauty, but for the personal connections they forge with this magnificent tree. I‚Äôve seen people leave behind tokens‚Äîa painted rock, a love note, or a small memento‚Äîeach representing a moment of joy or a wish for the future. On my second visit, I joined a group of artists for a plein air painting session. The atmosphere was electric, filled with laughter and creativity as we each attempted to capture the tree‚Äôs essence. As I painted, I felt a connection to those who had come before me, each brushstroke a tribute to the tree‚Äôs enduring legacy.

The Great Shelford Tree also serves as a hub for the community. Throughout the year, various events take place around this majestic tree‚Äîseasonal festivals, quaint gatherings, and meditation sessions. The camaraderie is palpable as friends connect over their love for this natural wonder.

One of the most poignant aspects of the Great Shelford Tree is its capacity for reflection. Standing beneath its vast canopy, I often contemplate my life journey. In a world that feels overwhelming, this tree offers grounding and peace. It has become a personal sanctuary where I can escape the hustle and bustle of daily life.

For those seeking inspiration, solace, or a simple moment of connection with nature, the Great Shelford Tree is an essential stop. It‚Äôs not just a tourist attraction; it‚Äôs a life-changing experience that encourages you to slow down, appreciate the beauty around you, and forge connections‚Äîwith both nature and those around you.

If you find yourself in the vicinity, I urge you to pay a visit. Bring a journal, a sketchbook, or simply your thoughts. You may leave with a renewed sense of purpose or just a smile, knowing you‚Äôve encountered something truly special. The Great Shelford Tree isn‚Äôt just a tree; it‚Äôs a monument to life itself, waiting to share its wisdom with anyone willing to listen.

Friendly doctor but didn‚Äôt give a correct diagnosis, I guess? Told the doctor previously I had fever and felt better but my mucus had pus from my throat‚Äôs inflammation which causes a rotten egg smell. Doctor deemed it as viral infection instead of bacteria-related. Thus, I was only prescribed with anti-Inflammation medicine but no anti-biotic.

text:
EVEYONE ESPECIALLY UNCLES AND AUNTYS! THIS IS A SCAM SHOP! Don't be fooled by the reviews!

My grandfather went to this shop for help with his SIM card issue. He had accidentally blocked his SIM by entering the wrong PUK code. The proper procedure would have been to resolve the SIM card issue or replace it, but instead, the shop dismantled every component of his phone and then put it back together again. They charged my grandfather $30 without even solving the SIM card problem.

Is it right to scam the elderly like this? I'm concerned that this shop is located in a mature estate. How many more elderly people are they going to exploit?

Datuk saya pergi ke kedai ini untuk mendapatkan bantuan mengenai isu kad SIMnya. Dia telah menyekat SIMnya secara tidak sengaja dengan memasukkan kod PUK yang salah. Mereka mengenakan bayaran kepada datuk saya SGD 30 tanpa menyelesaikan masalah kad SIM.

title: CS Fresh @ Holland Shopping Centre
text:
I was shopping here a few days ago when a Tillamook Cheese Promoter asked me if I wanted to sample their cheese.

I was trying to be polite by making a small talk with her, so I casually asked her if Tillamook is a new Cheese brand. But her response really shocked me.

She turned her head in a dramatic slow-mo, rolled her eyes at me as she said ‚Äúhuhhh‚Ä¶‚Ä¶?‚Äù ‚Äúno‚Ä¶..?‚Äù ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs been around for so long already, you didn‚Äôt hear before meh?‚Äù She said so much yet she could not tell me exactly which year was the brand founded.

So she was rude and judgmental towards me when I have not heard of the brand, yet she herself as a promoter of Tillamook, don‚Äôt know when it‚Äôs founded?

Isn‚Äôt the point of being a promoter, to promote and share more about the brand to customers? What‚Äôs the point of hiring one when the promoter was so judgemental yet clueless about the brand?

I‚Äôm sure the reason why she‚Äôs even hired to promote at the temporary booth at CS is because the brand is unpopular and they want to make it known to CS customers, so it‚Äôs not surprising that I haven‚Äôt heard of the brand.

This encounter with the female promoter really ruined my shopping experience at CS. I‚Äôd rather patronise Fairprice Finest in future.

Edit: Just to add that I‚Äôve sent a feedback to CS via email and their response felt really templated and insincere. I‚Äôm just disappointed.

title: Samsung Service Centre Westgate
text:
Zero stars.. This is hands down one of the most frustrating and painful service experiences I‚Äôve had. I brought in a Samsung device for what should have been a straightforward power button repair. I was first quoted around $200, then later received a text saying that the cost had increased to over $400‚Äîwith no proper explanation.

When I finally received a call, I was told the technician had now found the touchscreen to be ‚Äúfaulty.‚Äù How convenient‚Äîthis issue only appeared after they disassembled the device. I was then told they couldn‚Äôt perform a partial repair just for the power button, so I‚Äôd have to pay for the screen as well.

Over the phone, I specifically asked multiple times if my device would be returned in the same condition if I didn‚Äôt proceed and the person acknowledged that it would, and I made my expectations very clear. Even before sending it in, I made this expectation known‚Äîbut now, of course, no one will admit to it.

When I didn‚Äôt proceed with the repair and came to collect my device, I checked and had to ask them to charge and demonstrate it‚Äîand that‚Äôs when it was revealed the screen wasn‚Äôt even showing the charging indicator anymore.

Here‚Äôs the worst part‚Äîwhen they tried to justify it, they told me that fixing the button would ‚Äúunavoidably‚Äù damage the touchscreen, meaning I‚Äôd be forced to pay for both. If that was the case, WHY wasn‚Äôt it disclosed upfront? Why quote one thing, then hold my device hostage with unexpected, unexplained charges?

Zero transparency. No accountability. The responses felt scripted, and the way things were handled left me, the customer, feeling like I was somehow at fault for not asking the ‚Äúright‚Äù questions‚Äîwhen I had, multiple times. Save yourself the trouble. Don‚Äôt send your device here unless you‚Äôre ready to be overcharged, misled, and left angry and helpless.

title: SkyHelix Sentosa
text:
SkyHelix Sentosa Review: A Decent Experience, But Not for Thrill-Seekers

We visited SkyHelix Sentosa in the morning, hoping for something fun or unique, but left feeling a bit underwhelmed.

The experience involves sitting in a parachute-like open-air gondola that slowly ascends into the sky and gently rotates to offer a 360¬∞ view of Sentosa. It lasts about 10-15 minutes. During that time, an instructor gives a short introduction and tries to entertain the group, which was nice, but there‚Äôs only so much you can do in that span, especially when the ride itself is very passive.

This is not a ride or anything adventurous. There‚Äôs no adrenaline rush, no surprises, just a slow ascent, a calm view, and a slow descent. The view in the morning was okay, but not particularly spectacular. Maybe a sunset or night session would be better for photography or ambiance.

That said, this attraction is suitable for people who aren‚Äôt into adventure or thrill rides and are just looking for a mild, scenic experience. It's peaceful and easy, making it ideal for families with young kids or older folks who want a simple, elevated view of the island.

Overall, it‚Äôs a decent, short activity, but if you're someone looking for excitement, SkyHelix probably won't deliver that.
